WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.379 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.379 --> 00:00:10.269 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:10.269 --> 00:00:28.082 align:middle line:90%


00:00:28.082 --> 00:00:30.540 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA MEREDITH: Nearly 30
years ago, I produced a series

00:00:30.540 --> 00:00:32.659 align:middle line:10%
on the nightly news
about using psychics

00:00:32.659 --> 00:00:34.560 align:middle line:10%
effectively to solve crime.

00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:37.140 align:middle line:84%
Still, this has not become
a mainstream practice

00:00:37.140 --> 00:00:38.660 align:middle line:84%
due to the prejudice
about dipping

00:00:38.660 --> 00:00:41.420 align:middle line:84%
into the less understood
world of the psyche.

00:00:41.420 --> 00:00:43.680 align:middle line:84%
Fortunately, the practice
hasn't gone away.

00:00:43.680 --> 00:00:46.320 align:middle line:84%
And one might argue it
should be on the increase

00:00:46.320 --> 00:00:49.370 align:middle line:84%
when it comes to adding new
clues to a case gone cold.

00:00:49.370 --> 00:00:52.400 align:middle line:84%
We have with us today Robbie
Thomas, a lifelong crime

00:00:52.400 --> 00:00:54.190 align:middle line:84%
fighter, using his
intuitive skills

00:00:54.190 --> 00:00:59.430 align:middle line:84%
to help solve what has been
insolvable or unsolvable.

00:00:59.430 --> 00:01:00.520 align:middle line:90%
I love your hat.

00:01:00.520 --> 00:01:02.070 align:middle line:90%
>>ROBBIE THOMAS: Thank you.

00:01:02.070 --> 00:01:02.690 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:01:02.690 --> 00:01:04.879 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, and your
earrings and your tattoos.

00:01:04.879 --> 00:01:06.480 align:middle line:84%
You're quite the
picture-- beautiful.

00:01:06.480 --> 00:01:07.240 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Whole nine yards.

00:01:07.240 --> 00:01:08.198 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: There you go.

00:01:08.198 --> 00:01:10.500 align:middle line:84%
So first of all-- I mean,
we have a fair amount

00:01:10.500 --> 00:01:11.920 align:middle line:84%
to talk about
today, so I thought

00:01:11.920 --> 00:01:15.990 align:middle line:84%
we would start when
you were a little kid.

00:01:15.990 --> 00:01:19.289 align:middle line:84%
You look like a guy that
should be on a Harley, right?

00:01:19.289 --> 00:01:21.080 align:middle line:84%
And maybe you are on
a Harley, but the fact

00:01:21.080 --> 00:01:22.630 align:middle line:84%
is you're surrounded
with daughters,

00:01:22.630 --> 00:01:25.070 align:middle line:84%
and you've always
been super sensitive,

00:01:25.070 --> 00:01:27.530 align:middle line:84%
and you were very sensitive
toward your mother as well.

00:01:27.530 --> 00:01:30.260 align:middle line:84%
And let's talk about stuff from
when you were a little kid.

00:01:30.260 --> 00:01:32.120 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Absolutely.

00:01:32.120 --> 00:01:34.610 align:middle line:10%
Being the age of two and
three, you're inquisitive,

00:01:34.610 --> 00:01:36.750 align:middle line:10%
you're a child, and you're
always poking your nose

00:01:36.750 --> 00:01:37.750 align:middle line:10%
into everything.

00:01:37.750 --> 00:01:39.605 align:middle line:10%
So I would approach
my mother at times

00:01:39.605 --> 00:01:42.170 align:middle line:10%
and say, either I'm
adopted or I have someone

00:01:42.170 --> 00:01:44.340 align:middle line:10%
out there who's a part
of me and adopted.

00:01:44.340 --> 00:01:46.200 align:middle line:84%
And she'd say, Ron--
that's my father's

00:01:46.200 --> 00:01:47.460 align:middle line:90%
name-- he's doing it again.

00:01:47.460 --> 00:01:50.530 align:middle line:84%
My father would say, Robbie,
quit it and get in here.

00:01:50.530 --> 00:01:52.220 align:middle line:90%
So then it would stop.

00:01:52.220 --> 00:01:54.140 align:middle line:84%
And then again, I would
approach my mother

00:01:54.140 --> 00:01:59.490 align:middle line:84%
and keep poking at her about
either a part of me out there.

00:01:59.490 --> 00:02:03.880 align:middle line:84%
Take you full circle to
1994, my mom passed away.

00:02:03.880 --> 00:02:06.440 align:middle line:84%
My family pulled
me aside and said,

00:02:06.440 --> 00:02:08.300 align:middle line:90%
she's been looking for you.

00:02:08.300 --> 00:02:10.180 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't understand
because I'm still

00:02:10.180 --> 00:02:11.839 align:middle line:84%
distraught from
my mother passing.

00:02:11.839 --> 00:02:13.755 align:middle line:84%
And they said, no, she's
been looking for you,

00:02:13.755 --> 00:02:15.820 align:middle line:84%
and she's the spitting
image of your mom.

00:02:15.820 --> 00:02:19.400 align:middle line:84%
So her name's Mary, and so
I got introduced to Mary.

00:02:19.400 --> 00:02:20.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Who said this?

00:02:20.640 --> 00:02:24.139 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: I'm sorry, my
mom's brother and sister.

00:02:24.139 --> 00:02:24.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:02:24.680 --> 00:02:25.530 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: After the funeral.

00:02:25.530 --> 00:02:26.605 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: After the funeral, OK.

00:02:26.605 --> 00:02:27.230 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah.

00:02:27.230 --> 00:02:31.760 align:middle line:84%
And so I met my sister for the
first time in all those years.

00:02:31.760 --> 00:02:37.630 align:middle line:84%
And so now going back to
being that nosy child,

00:02:37.630 --> 00:02:39.430 align:middle line:84%
it kind of paid
off, because that's

00:02:39.430 --> 00:02:42.150 align:middle line:84%
when I was sensing and
being told that there was

00:02:42.150 --> 00:02:43.359 align:middle line:90%
another part of me out there.

00:02:43.359 --> 00:02:44.358 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Where was she?

00:02:44.358 --> 00:02:45.770 align:middle line:84%
What had happened
to your sister?

00:02:45.770 --> 00:02:47.910 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Back in
the early '60s,

00:02:47.910 --> 00:02:52.050 align:middle line:84%
Roman Catholic-- the church,
my mother being unwed,

00:02:52.050 --> 00:02:53.380 align:middle line:90%
became pregnant.

00:02:53.380 --> 00:02:55.440 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You went to a
home, and then the kids

00:02:55.440 --> 00:02:56.350 align:middle line:90%
were adopted out.

00:02:56.350 --> 00:02:57.016 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Right.

00:02:57.016 --> 00:02:58.880 align:middle line:90%
So they took her daughter.

00:02:58.880 --> 00:03:02.570 align:middle line:84%
And then years later,
she met my father,

00:03:02.570 --> 00:03:05.170 align:middle line:84%
married him, and had me, the
one who was poking his nose.

00:03:05.170 --> 00:03:05.880 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:03:05.880 --> 00:03:08.494 align:middle line:84%
But you were still feeling
like there was something,

00:03:08.494 --> 00:03:09.660 align:middle line:90%
you had a sibling out there.

00:03:09.660 --> 00:03:12.076 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: There was something
out there, yeah, absolutely.

00:03:12.076 --> 00:03:14.640 align:middle line:84%
And so come full
circle, I meet Mary,

00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:17.630 align:middle line:84%
and then FOX Radio
does this big special

00:03:17.630 --> 00:03:22.300 align:middle line:84%
in 1994, which was uplifting,
because I lost a piece of me

00:03:22.300 --> 00:03:23.900 align:middle line:90%
and then I gained a piece of me.

00:03:23.900 --> 00:03:25.990 align:middle line:84%
And it was something like
a present left behind

00:03:25.990 --> 00:03:27.050 align:middle line:90%
for me from my mother.

00:03:27.050 --> 00:03:28.424 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And
there was something

00:03:28.424 --> 00:03:31.770 align:middle line:84%
surrounding your mother's
departure as well, as I recall.

00:03:31.770 --> 00:03:32.630 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yes.

00:03:32.630 --> 00:03:35.930 align:middle line:90%
And we all have our signs.

00:03:35.930 --> 00:03:40.100 align:middle line:84%
And so this sign was the
night prior to her passing,

00:03:40.100 --> 00:03:42.550 align:middle line:84%
which they said her
cancer was cured.

00:03:42.550 --> 00:03:43.550 align:middle line:90%
Everything was fine.

00:03:43.550 --> 00:03:44.760 align:middle line:90%
I met with the doctors.

00:03:44.760 --> 00:03:47.051 align:middle line:84%
I was the one who was taking
her down for her radiation

00:03:47.051 --> 00:03:47.860 align:middle line:90%
treatments.

00:03:47.860 --> 00:03:49.820 align:middle line:84%
And so they said
she's in remission.

00:03:49.820 --> 00:03:51.420 align:middle line:90%
Everything's fine.

00:03:51.420 --> 00:03:54.970 align:middle line:84%
Come that night, it was
almost like a suppression.

00:03:54.970 --> 00:03:57.050 align:middle line:84%
I know a lot of people
can relate to this, where

00:03:57.050 --> 00:03:59.270 align:middle line:90%
they feel they're trapped.

00:03:59.270 --> 00:04:00.470 align:middle line:90%
They can't move.

00:04:00.470 --> 00:04:02.210 align:middle line:90%
They're struggling.

00:04:02.210 --> 00:04:04.969 align:middle line:84%
And they're having an
apparition or a vision to them.

00:04:04.969 --> 00:04:06.260 align:middle line:90%
Well, it was the four horsemen.

00:04:06.260 --> 00:04:08.060 align:middle line:84%
And the one horseman
was in white and said,

00:04:08.060 --> 00:04:09.520 align:middle line:90%
there's nothing to worry about.

00:04:09.520 --> 00:04:10.950 align:middle line:90%
You'll be taken care of.

00:04:10.950 --> 00:04:14.020 align:middle line:84%
And then he showed me what
was going to happen that day.

00:04:14.020 --> 00:04:19.029 align:middle line:84%
After that moment with them
and coming to the morning,

00:04:19.029 --> 00:04:20.404 align:middle line:84%
I usually go to
my mother's house

00:04:20.404 --> 00:04:22.630 align:middle line:84%
for coffee-- I'm a
mommy's boy-- and have

00:04:22.630 --> 00:04:24.710 align:middle line:90%
tea or coffee or toast.

00:04:24.710 --> 00:04:27.900 align:middle line:84%
And I approached into her
kitchen, sat down in the chair,

00:04:27.900 --> 00:04:28.910 align:middle line:90%
and I addressed to her.

00:04:28.910 --> 00:04:31.106 align:middle line:84%
She's not looking
at me, and I said,

00:04:31.106 --> 00:04:32.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm compelled to have
to tell you this.

00:04:32.730 --> 00:04:34.590 align:middle line:84%
And I explained what
happened last night.

00:04:34.590 --> 00:04:37.450 align:middle line:84%
She said to me, well,
you go come home,

00:04:37.450 --> 00:04:40.900 align:middle line:84%
and I'll call you later
to watch your daughter.

00:04:40.900 --> 00:04:44.810 align:middle line:84%
And so I felt kind of funny,
how she's asking me to leave.

00:04:44.810 --> 00:04:46.520 align:middle line:84%
But it's that
push-pull factor, where

00:04:46.520 --> 00:04:50.500 align:middle line:84%
you know you want to stay
because there's an urgency,

00:04:50.500 --> 00:04:52.590 align:middle line:84%
but you have to leave
because you've been asked.

00:04:52.590 --> 00:04:54.290 align:middle line:90%
So I leave.

00:04:54.290 --> 00:04:56.310 align:middle line:90%
Nonetheless, I'm at home.

00:04:56.310 --> 00:04:58.540 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sitting with my
wife, and my good friend

00:04:58.540 --> 00:04:59.340 align:middle line:90%
came over after.

00:04:59.340 --> 00:05:01.804 align:middle line:84%
And we're drinking coffee,
and the phone rings.

00:05:01.804 --> 00:05:03.470 align:middle line:84%
And it's about an
hour and a half later.

00:05:03.470 --> 00:05:05.467 align:middle line:84%
And my father's on the
other line screaming,

00:05:05.467 --> 00:05:06.175 align:middle line:90%
it's your mother!

00:05:06.175 --> 00:05:07.280 align:middle line:90%
It's your mother!

00:05:07.280 --> 00:05:09.000 align:middle line:90%
So we raced over.

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:11.715 align:middle line:84%
And what I remember is
the EMTs pulling her out

00:05:11.715 --> 00:05:14.170 align:middle line:84%
on the gurney, her
little purple sock,

00:05:14.170 --> 00:05:16.130 align:middle line:84%
her hand hanging over
the side, the one

00:05:16.130 --> 00:05:18.640 align:middle line:90%
EMT on top doing compressions.

00:05:18.640 --> 00:05:22.849 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, it was
that moment where--

00:05:22.849 --> 00:05:23.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: She knew.

00:05:23.640 --> 00:05:24.310 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: She knew.

00:05:24.310 --> 00:05:25.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: She asked you
to leave for a reason.

00:05:25.470 --> 00:05:26.100 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: She knew.

00:05:26.100 --> 00:05:26.599 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:05:26.599 --> 00:05:29.590 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And oftentimes
when people do pass,

00:05:29.590 --> 00:05:31.812 align:middle line:84%
it's when they're
alone and often

00:05:31.812 --> 00:05:33.770 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of the
night where there's no one

00:05:33.770 --> 00:05:36.580 align:middle line:84%
to create the drag on them
when they're trying to release

00:05:36.580 --> 00:05:38.020 align:middle line:90%
themselves from the body.

00:05:38.020 --> 00:05:39.410 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Right, right.

00:05:39.410 --> 00:05:43.460 align:middle line:84%
It's that integral moment when
spirit steps in and takes those

00:05:43.460 --> 00:05:47.660 align:middle line:84%
problems and those problematic
moments away from--

00:05:47.660 --> 00:05:49.717 align:middle line:84%
even the burden,
if you will, on--

00:05:49.717 --> 00:05:50.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:05:50.300 --> 00:05:50.540 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yes.

00:05:50.540 --> 00:05:52.210 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it's funny
because so many of us

00:05:52.210 --> 00:05:53.960 align:middle line:84%
think, oh, God, I don't
want to die alone.

00:05:53.960 --> 00:05:56.720 align:middle line:84%
Oh, I'd love for my children
to be with me or my husband

00:05:56.720 --> 00:05:57.860 align:middle line:90%
or wife or whatnot.

00:05:57.860 --> 00:06:00.140 align:middle line:84%
But then you slip away
at 2:00 in the morning

00:06:00.140 --> 00:06:02.360 align:middle line:84%
when nobody's
there, or whoever's

00:06:02.360 --> 00:06:05.290 align:middle line:84%
there is asleep in the
chair, because the soul needs

00:06:05.290 --> 00:06:06.232 align:middle line:90%
to do its own thing.

00:06:06.232 --> 00:06:07.190 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: That's right.

00:06:07.190 --> 00:06:09.023 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This is not
a sentimental process.

00:06:09.023 --> 00:06:09.620 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: No.

00:06:09.620 --> 00:06:10.120 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:06:10.120 --> 00:06:11.060 align:middle line:90%
It's not a project.

00:06:11.060 --> 00:06:13.125 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:06:13.125 --> 00:06:14.750 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: But yeah,
and that's perfect,

00:06:14.750 --> 00:06:16.980 align:middle line:84%
because it's like
signs from heaven.

00:06:16.980 --> 00:06:19.170 align:middle line:84%
And I speak very much
about signs from heaven

00:06:19.170 --> 00:06:21.400 align:middle line:84%
and how we're all
in this interlude

00:06:21.400 --> 00:06:24.880 align:middle line:84%
and how we have the
retainment, if you will,

00:06:24.880 --> 00:06:27.230 align:middle line:84%
of spirit, because we
have our spirit guides,

00:06:27.230 --> 00:06:32.600 align:middle line:84%
we have our angels, and they
do caress us, if you will,

00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:33.530 align:middle line:90%
all through our lives.

00:06:33.530 --> 00:06:36.830 align:middle line:84%
And it's a gradual
progression of atonement.

00:06:36.830 --> 00:06:38.050 align:middle line:90%
And it's how we are.

00:06:38.050 --> 00:06:38.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:06:38.970 --> 00:06:42.410 align:middle line:84%
And so this whole
notion of people leaving

00:06:42.410 --> 00:06:44.730 align:middle line:84%
their lives, a lot
of them in the cases

00:06:44.730 --> 00:06:48.210 align:middle line:84%
that you work on, violently,
people disappearing, people

00:06:48.210 --> 00:06:51.130 align:middle line:84%
being murdered, cases
that are difficult.

00:06:51.130 --> 00:06:53.270 align:middle line:84%
When Jerry Wills,
who I've interviewed,

00:06:53.270 --> 00:06:56.360 align:middle line:84%
first introduced
me to you, he said,

00:06:56.360 --> 00:07:01.580 align:middle line:84%
he's kind of like Allison
DuBois, but he's the real deal.

00:07:01.580 --> 00:07:02.860 align:middle line:90%
He's the real Medium.

00:07:02.860 --> 00:07:05.670 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: That's
quite the compliment.

00:07:05.670 --> 00:07:07.640 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But as a kid,
you knew right away

00:07:07.640 --> 00:07:10.210 align:middle line:90%
you wanted to be in crime.

00:07:10.210 --> 00:07:11.630 align:middle line:90%
You wanted to fight crime.

00:07:11.630 --> 00:07:13.880 align:middle line:90%
What was that in you?

00:07:13.880 --> 00:07:15.550 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: That in
me was a drive.

00:07:15.550 --> 00:07:16.430 align:middle line:90%
That was a drive.

00:07:16.430 --> 00:07:20.650 align:middle line:84%
There were two
professions, if you will.

00:07:20.650 --> 00:07:25.440 align:middle line:84%
Father Pidelt had a very
overbearing draw to me,

00:07:25.440 --> 00:07:28.420 align:middle line:84%
and I was so much wanting
to be a priest when

00:07:28.420 --> 00:07:29.800 align:middle line:90%
I was a young child.

00:07:29.800 --> 00:07:32.890 align:middle line:84%
And then I didn't understand
why they spoke Latin facing away

00:07:32.890 --> 00:07:36.440 align:middle line:84%
from you, or to you, or they
turned and they were away.

00:07:36.440 --> 00:07:39.080 align:middle line:84%
Then they sung different
things in church.

00:07:39.080 --> 00:07:42.920 align:middle line:84%
And growing up, I kind
of have my own grievances

00:07:42.920 --> 00:07:44.220 align:middle line:90%
of why they would do that.

00:07:44.220 --> 00:07:45.770 align:middle line:90%
And it was an inner struggle.

00:07:45.770 --> 00:07:47.600 align:middle line:84%
So then I wanted to
be a police officer.

00:07:47.600 --> 00:07:50.300 align:middle line:84%
So then I want through to
be a police officer twice,

00:07:50.300 --> 00:07:51.882 align:middle line:90%
hired and fired in one day.

00:07:51.882 --> 00:07:53.840 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah talk about
that, how you somehow

00:07:53.840 --> 00:07:56.700 align:middle line:84%
got under the wire as
an underage young man.

00:07:56.700 --> 00:07:57.940 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yes, I did.

00:07:57.940 --> 00:08:00.640 align:middle line:90%
I infiltrated the police.

00:08:00.640 --> 00:08:03.210 align:middle line:84%
And it's funny, because
I did all the testing.

00:08:03.210 --> 00:08:05.780 align:middle line:90%
I did all the written part.

00:08:05.780 --> 00:08:08.100 align:middle line:84%
And they were taking three
auxiliaries that day.

00:08:08.100 --> 00:08:11.682 align:middle line:84%
So I'm in Chief Cook's office,
and we're signing papers.

00:08:11.682 --> 00:08:12.890 align:middle line:90%
He does the other two fellas.

00:08:12.890 --> 00:08:13.780 align:middle line:90%
I let them go first.

00:08:13.780 --> 00:08:15.988 align:middle line:84%
And then he looks at mine
and sees the date of birth,

00:08:15.988 --> 00:08:18.490 align:middle line:84%
and he just had a big
chuckle and he said, son,

00:08:18.490 --> 00:08:20.550 align:middle line:90%
you come back when you're 20.

00:08:20.550 --> 00:08:22.183 align:middle line:84%
I looked 20 because
I had a moustache.

00:08:22.183 --> 00:08:24.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: [LAUGHING] And
you were 17 years old.

00:08:24.240 --> 00:08:26.010 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: I was 17 years of age.

00:08:26.010 --> 00:08:28.034 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so let's
talk-- so you came back.

00:08:28.034 --> 00:08:28.950 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: I came back.

00:08:28.950 --> 00:08:30.284 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, OK.

00:08:30.284 --> 00:08:31.450 align:middle line:90%
Let's pick it up from there.

00:08:31.450 --> 00:08:32.761 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Sure.

00:08:32.761 --> 00:08:34.469 align:middle line:84%
I went through to be
a police officer out

00:08:34.469 --> 00:08:38.570 align:middle line:84%
of a town outside of Toronto,
Canada, Peel Regional Police.

00:08:38.570 --> 00:08:42.520 align:middle line:84%
I got hired on, did the final
brass interviews, come home.

00:08:42.520 --> 00:08:44.720 align:middle line:84%
I'm elated, tired
from all the testing

00:08:44.720 --> 00:08:47.650 align:middle line:84%
days of doing the physical
and then the written.

00:08:47.650 --> 00:08:49.600 align:middle line:90%
I finally come home.

00:08:49.600 --> 00:08:51.660 align:middle line:84%
I'm sitting in the
kitchen, and I hear,

00:08:51.660 --> 00:08:53.910 align:middle line:90%
accident, accident, screaming.

00:08:53.910 --> 00:08:55.850 align:middle line:84%
And it was a lady
behind the fence

00:08:55.850 --> 00:08:58.110 align:middle line:84%
of my home in the
townhomes that were

00:08:58.110 --> 00:09:00.670 align:middle line:90%
running like this to the road.

00:09:00.670 --> 00:09:03.520 align:middle line:84%
So I hopped the fence, and first
thing is a reaction to help.

00:09:03.520 --> 00:09:06.830 align:middle line:84%
So I'm looking at her, and
she's pointing down the laneway.

00:09:06.830 --> 00:09:09.310 align:middle line:84%
So I run that direction,
and I'm thinking

00:09:09.310 --> 00:09:11.670 align:middle line:84%
car accident because that's
all I heard, was "accident."

00:09:11.670 --> 00:09:12.669 align:middle line:90%
And I look out the road.

00:09:12.669 --> 00:09:13.770 align:middle line:90%
There's no cars.

00:09:13.770 --> 00:09:14.902 align:middle line:90%
Traffic's fine.

00:09:14.902 --> 00:09:16.360 align:middle line:84%
Then I look to my
left, and there's

00:09:16.360 --> 00:09:18.077 align:middle line:90%
a gentleman by the screen door.

00:09:18.077 --> 00:09:19.160 align:middle line:90%
And he's going, come here.

00:09:19.160 --> 00:09:20.930 align:middle line:90%
He's waving me over like this.

00:09:20.930 --> 00:09:22.930 align:middle line:90%
So I run over to him.

00:09:22.930 --> 00:09:24.955 align:middle line:84%
I walk into the
kitchen area, and there

00:09:24.955 --> 00:09:28.110 align:middle line:84%
was a lady to the left running
around the table screaming.

00:09:28.110 --> 00:09:30.640 align:middle line:84%
And there was a gentleman to
my right holding a doorknob.

00:09:30.640 --> 00:09:31.840 align:middle line:90%
And he says, come here.

00:09:31.840 --> 00:09:35.210 align:middle line:84%
So I go over to him, he grabs
my shoulder, opens the door,

00:09:35.210 --> 00:09:37.180 align:middle line:90%
shoves me in, shuts the door.

00:09:37.180 --> 00:09:40.150 align:middle line:84%
So now I'm still
thinking accident.

00:09:40.150 --> 00:09:42.590 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking for
blood on the floor.

00:09:42.590 --> 00:09:44.440 align:middle line:84%
And I look up, and
there's a gentleman.

00:09:44.440 --> 00:09:48.690 align:middle line:84%
And he's sitting in the
bathroom, and he's passed.

00:09:48.690 --> 00:09:53.220 align:middle line:84%
But his eyes are gone
directly on to me.

00:09:53.220 --> 00:09:53.870 align:middle line:90%
Unnerving.

00:09:53.870 --> 00:09:55.800 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Unnerving, yes.

00:09:55.800 --> 00:09:56.750 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: [LAUGHING] To
say the least, right?

00:09:56.750 --> 00:09:58.710 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Even if no one's
home, someone was around.

00:09:58.710 --> 00:09:59.876 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah, yeah, right.

00:09:59.876 --> 00:10:03.920 align:middle line:84%
So out the window goes all this
bravado of everything, right?

00:10:03.920 --> 00:10:07.550 align:middle line:84%
And then right away,
CPR, check for vitals.

00:10:07.550 --> 00:10:08.410 align:middle line:90%
So I run over.

00:10:08.410 --> 00:10:09.920 align:middle line:90%
I see his lips are blue.

00:10:09.920 --> 00:10:11.920 align:middle line:90%
And he's kind of pale.

00:10:11.920 --> 00:10:16.130 align:middle line:84%
I check for vitals,
and I start to do CPR.

00:10:16.130 --> 00:10:19.594 align:middle line:84%
No sooner do I start doing
CPR, I hear, let me go.

00:10:19.594 --> 00:10:21.510 align:middle line:84%
So I step back for a
moment, and I'm thinking,

00:10:21.510 --> 00:10:24.190 align:middle line:84%
this is my imagination,
and then, no.

00:10:24.190 --> 00:10:28.235 align:middle line:84%
So I go back right away again
and touch for vitals, CPR.

00:10:28.235 --> 00:10:30.940 align:middle line:84%
And I hear it really
loud, clears as a bell,

00:10:30.940 --> 00:10:33.190 align:middle line:90%
let me go, deep voice.

00:10:33.190 --> 00:10:34.285 align:middle line:90%
I stop.

00:10:34.285 --> 00:10:35.200 align:middle line:90%
I back up.

00:10:35.200 --> 00:10:36.420 align:middle line:90%
I walk out the door.

00:10:36.420 --> 00:10:37.730 align:middle line:90%
And everybody's standing there.

00:10:37.730 --> 00:10:39.870 align:middle line:90%
Now there's not three people.

00:10:39.870 --> 00:10:42.625 align:middle line:84%
There's a ton of people, and
they're all staring at me.

00:10:42.625 --> 00:10:46.060 align:middle line:84%
And I just shake my head like
this, and that put everything

00:10:46.060 --> 00:10:48.530 align:middle line:90%
in an uproar, right?

00:10:48.530 --> 00:10:51.190 align:middle line:84%
Turns out it was my
sister's best friend's

00:10:51.190 --> 00:10:53.660 align:middle line:90%
father, a small world.

00:10:53.660 --> 00:10:57.380 align:middle line:84%
And from that moment on, I
knew I had a different route

00:10:57.380 --> 00:10:58.987 align:middle line:90%
to take.

00:10:58.987 --> 00:11:00.403 align:middle line:84%
I call up, and I
say, I don't want

00:11:00.403 --> 00:11:02.130 align:middle line:90%
to be a police officer no more.

00:11:02.130 --> 00:11:03.630 align:middle line:90%
You just don't quit.

00:11:03.630 --> 00:11:04.810 align:middle line:90%
They want to know why.

00:11:04.810 --> 00:11:08.260 align:middle line:84%
So they sent the captain,
a sergeant from the Chatham

00:11:08.260 --> 00:11:12.480 align:middle line:84%
police force-- it's in
Ontario-- a film crew.

00:11:12.480 --> 00:11:14.490 align:middle line:90%
And they come into my home.

00:11:14.490 --> 00:11:15.990 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That was presumptuous.

00:11:15.990 --> 00:11:17.490 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah.

00:11:17.490 --> 00:11:19.520 align:middle line:90%
They want to know why you quit.

00:11:19.520 --> 00:11:23.740 align:middle line:84%
And so they said,
we're doing a movie

00:11:23.740 --> 00:11:27.325 align:middle line:84%
on first responders
who quit under duress.

00:11:27.325 --> 00:11:29.940 align:middle line:84%
And we'd like you to
be part of this model.

00:11:29.940 --> 00:11:31.380 align:middle line:90%
So I agreed.

00:11:31.380 --> 00:11:32.920 align:middle line:90%
And I wasn't stressed.

00:11:32.920 --> 00:11:34.866 align:middle line:84%
I just went, all
right, come in my home.

00:11:34.866 --> 00:11:36.740 align:middle line:84%
So they did, and they
asked me the questions.

00:11:36.740 --> 00:11:39.822 align:middle line:84%
So I answered vigorously
and straightforward.

00:11:39.822 --> 00:11:41.280 align:middle line:84%
Well, you should
have seen the look

00:11:41.280 --> 00:11:43.820 align:middle line:84%
on their face and their
jaws, because when I said,

00:11:43.820 --> 00:11:46.606 align:middle line:84%
he said let me go, and
I'm hearing this man,

00:11:46.606 --> 00:11:48.480 align:middle line:84%
it's not because I'm
quitting because I don't

00:11:48.480 --> 00:11:49.720 align:middle line:90%
want to be a police officer.

00:11:49.720 --> 00:11:50.950 align:middle line:90%
I just found my direction.

00:11:50.950 --> 00:11:53.440 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's a wrap,
and I'm in that movie,

00:11:53.440 --> 00:11:56.460 align:middle line:84%
and that's 20-some years
ago, the first one.

00:11:56.460 --> 00:11:58.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Tell us
about the movie.

00:11:58.460 --> 00:12:01.080 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: It's first
responders, EMTs, firefighters,

00:12:01.080 --> 00:12:03.740 align:middle line:84%
and police officers,
who quit under duress,

00:12:03.740 --> 00:12:08.340 align:middle line:84%
stressful situations of people
being murdered or finding

00:12:08.340 --> 00:12:11.020 align:middle line:84%
people dead or
just the job itself

00:12:11.020 --> 00:12:13.060 align:middle line:90%
in association to your life.

00:12:13.060 --> 00:12:15.054 align:middle line:90%
So I'm just part of that movie.

00:12:15.054 --> 00:12:15.720 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mmhmm.

00:12:15.720 --> 00:12:18.920 align:middle line:84%
Now, you seem so-- well,
you are very sensitive

00:12:18.920 --> 00:12:21.160 align:middle line:84%
or you wouldn't be
able to do what you do.

00:12:21.160 --> 00:12:22.120 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Right.

00:12:22.120 --> 00:12:24.900 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Did you want to be
toting a gun and on the street

00:12:24.900 --> 00:12:26.576 align:middle line:84%
and doing that sort
of thing, really,

00:12:26.576 --> 00:12:32.680 align:middle line:84%
or was it a back door into what
you ultimately ended up doing?

00:12:32.680 --> 00:12:36.170 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: I don't like
hurting people, toting a gun.

00:12:36.170 --> 00:12:39.816 align:middle line:84%
And I know you know,
reference to that.

00:12:39.816 --> 00:12:42.390 align:middle line:90%
It kind of doesn't sit well.

00:12:42.390 --> 00:12:44.610 align:middle line:84%
So I still wanted to
be a police officer.

00:12:44.610 --> 00:12:45.960 align:middle line:90%
I want to do what's right.

00:12:45.960 --> 00:12:48.620 align:middle line:84%
I want what is right
has to be right.

00:12:48.620 --> 00:12:51.790 align:middle line:90%
And let's face it.

00:12:51.790 --> 00:12:55.300 align:middle line:84%
In any profession there's bad
doctors, there's bad lawyers,

00:12:55.300 --> 00:12:57.040 align:middle line:90%
there's bad police officers.

00:12:57.040 --> 00:12:58.670 align:middle line:90%
But I was straightforward.

00:12:58.670 --> 00:13:00.670 align:middle line:84%
I remember getting into
an interview one time.

00:13:00.670 --> 00:13:05.090 align:middle line:84%
It was Chief Lunn in Wallaceburg
in a place where actually I

00:13:05.090 --> 00:13:08.950 align:middle line:84%
helped out in a missing
boy's case not too long ago.

00:13:08.950 --> 00:13:13.350 align:middle line:84%
And going back those many
years, he said to me,

00:13:13.350 --> 00:13:16.370 align:middle line:84%
one day you're going to be
one heck of a police officer.

00:13:16.370 --> 00:13:18.950 align:middle line:84%
And I just didn't make
it that time for him,

00:13:18.950 --> 00:13:22.650 align:middle line:84%
but yeah, it's just
the drive and wanting

00:13:22.650 --> 00:13:24.292 align:middle line:90%
to help and service.

00:13:24.292 --> 00:13:25.250 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right wrongs.

00:13:25.250 --> 00:13:28.330 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Yeah, right
the wrongs and do right.

00:13:28.330 --> 00:13:31.490 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So at what point
did you realize you really

00:13:31.490 --> 00:13:33.970 align:middle line:84%
did have something
special going on

00:13:33.970 --> 00:13:36.570 align:middle line:84%
with solving these very
difficult cases, particularly

00:13:36.570 --> 00:13:38.580 align:middle line:90%
homicide?

00:13:38.580 --> 00:13:42.080 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Take you
back to my first one.

00:13:42.080 --> 00:13:47.390 align:middle line:84%
Standing in the parking lot of
an apartment building speaking

00:13:47.390 --> 00:13:50.910 align:middle line:84%
with a friend of mine, and I
see this gentleman walk maybe 50

00:13:50.910 --> 00:13:53.190 align:middle line:84%
yards behind him, going
across the parking lot,

00:13:53.190 --> 00:13:54.930 align:middle line:84%
going into the
apartment building.

00:13:54.930 --> 00:13:56.849 align:middle line:90%
I see a black shroud around him.

00:13:56.849 --> 00:13:59.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I'm going to ask
more about that in a minute.

00:13:59.140 --> 00:14:00.020 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Sure.

00:14:00.020 --> 00:14:03.160 align:middle line:90%
And when I see black, it's bad.

00:14:03.160 --> 00:14:06.630 align:middle line:84%
And it's a draw, a strong
draw, because I'm inquisitive.

00:14:06.630 --> 00:14:07.970 align:middle line:90%
And I could feel it.

00:14:07.970 --> 00:14:10.650 align:middle line:84%
And you feel it in here
that there's something

00:14:10.650 --> 00:14:12.480 align:middle line:90%
wrong with that person.

00:14:12.480 --> 00:14:16.182 align:middle line:84%
So as Greg's talking to me,
he's noticing my eye movement,

00:14:16.182 --> 00:14:17.890 align:middle line:84%
and he turns over his
shoulder and looks,

00:14:17.890 --> 00:14:19.864 align:middle line:90%
and he goes, oh, that's Jesse.

00:14:19.864 --> 00:14:21.530 align:middle line:84%
And he goes, do you
want to go meet him?

00:14:21.530 --> 00:14:24.160 align:middle line:84%
But by that time, he's
already in the building.

00:14:24.160 --> 00:14:25.215 align:middle line:90%
I said, sure.

00:14:25.215 --> 00:14:26.590 align:middle line:84%
So we started to
go up to Jesse--

00:14:26.590 --> 00:14:27.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Just out of curiosity?

00:14:27.580 --> 00:14:29.290 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Yeah, for
me out of curiosity.

00:14:29.290 --> 00:14:29.780 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah,
because you don't

00:14:29.780 --> 00:14:31.470 align:middle line:90%
see black auras that often.

00:14:31.470 --> 00:14:35.190 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Not too often,
but people who are bad, bad,

00:14:35.190 --> 00:14:36.430 align:middle line:90%
you do see them.

00:14:36.430 --> 00:14:38.815 align:middle line:84%
It's like you can read
people for who they are.

00:14:38.815 --> 00:14:39.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:14:39.690 --> 00:14:42.690 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: So we ended up
in his apartment building.

00:14:42.690 --> 00:14:45.590 align:middle line:84%
I don't kind of remember how
we got in there, but we did.

00:14:45.590 --> 00:14:47.500 align:middle line:84%
And my line of
questioning to him

00:14:47.500 --> 00:14:52.229 align:middle line:84%
was straightforward, more
along the cop line, hard-nosed.

00:14:52.229 --> 00:14:53.770 align:middle line:84%
And if you could
picture an Eddie Van

00:14:53.770 --> 00:14:58.870 align:middle line:84%
Halen, sawed-off, 5-foot,
perfect image, the same guy,

00:14:58.870 --> 00:15:01.310 align:middle line:90%
and he was sitting down.

00:15:01.310 --> 00:15:04.140 align:middle line:84%
And then he asked me-- and
I remember his girlfriend

00:15:04.140 --> 00:15:07.032 align:middle line:84%
behind him, and I can
see him in my head still.

00:15:07.032 --> 00:15:07.740 align:middle line:90%
She was pregnant.

00:15:07.740 --> 00:15:09.080 align:middle line:90%
She's pacing back and forth.

00:15:09.080 --> 00:15:10.262 align:middle line:90%
And I'm asking questions.

00:15:10.262 --> 00:15:11.970 align:middle line:84%
I don't remember the
line of questioning,

00:15:11.970 --> 00:15:13.510 align:middle line:90%
but I'm asking the questions.

00:15:13.510 --> 00:15:15.010 align:middle line:90%
And he stands up.

00:15:15.010 --> 00:15:16.270 align:middle line:90%
He goes, stand up.

00:15:16.270 --> 00:15:16.860 align:middle line:90%
So I did.

00:15:16.860 --> 00:15:19.387 align:middle line:90%
He goes, are you effing hot?

00:15:19.387 --> 00:15:20.970 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't understand
what he meant.

00:15:20.970 --> 00:15:23.390 align:middle line:84%
And then he grabs my
shirt, lifts it up.

00:15:23.390 --> 00:15:24.230 align:middle line:90%
Then I knew.

00:15:24.230 --> 00:15:25.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He wanted to
see if you had a wire.

00:15:25.360 --> 00:15:25.810 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Wire on.

00:15:25.810 --> 00:15:26.435 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:15:26.435 --> 00:15:27.130 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah.

00:15:27.130 --> 00:15:32.800 align:middle line:84%
And once I knew that, and he's
seen I had no wire, he goes,

00:15:32.800 --> 00:15:34.880 align:middle line:90%
you want to know what happened?

00:15:34.880 --> 00:15:36.780 align:middle line:84%
Mark was a young man
who move from Quebec

00:15:36.780 --> 00:15:38.424 align:middle line:90%
to Ontario with his family.

00:15:38.424 --> 00:15:39.590 align:middle line:90%
He was going to high school.

00:15:39.590 --> 00:15:40.548 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Who was Mark?

00:15:40.548 --> 00:15:43.400 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Mark is a young man
who was just a high school kid.

00:15:43.400 --> 00:15:45.150 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, he's
telling you this story?

00:15:45.150 --> 00:15:47.358 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Yeah, but he was
the one who was murdered--

00:15:47.358 --> 00:15:48.640 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, there you go.

00:15:48.640 --> 00:15:49.730 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: --by this gentleman.

00:15:49.730 --> 00:15:50.646 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: By this guy.

00:15:50.646 --> 00:15:52.430 align:middle line:90%
Jesse you said his name was?

00:15:52.430 --> 00:15:53.804 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Jesse, aka Jesse.

00:15:53.804 --> 00:15:55.345 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So Jesse
had murdered Mark,

00:15:55.345 --> 00:15:56.800 align:middle line:84%
and now he's going to
tell you what happened.

00:15:56.800 --> 00:15:57.740 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Right.

00:15:57.740 --> 00:16:03.100 align:middle line:84%
So he starts explaining Thomas
was his associate with him.

00:16:03.100 --> 00:16:06.440 align:middle line:84%
We're ripping off a car
stereo in the townhouses

00:16:06.440 --> 00:16:08.320 align:middle line:84%
across the way from
the gas station

00:16:08.320 --> 00:16:10.410 align:middle line:84%
that Mark was working to
make a little cash going

00:16:10.410 --> 00:16:12.320 align:middle line:90%
to school back then.

00:16:12.320 --> 00:16:16.960 align:middle line:84%
He said Thomas want to
go rob the gas station,

00:16:16.960 --> 00:16:18.945 align:middle line:90%
so they left there to go across.

00:16:18.945 --> 00:16:20.403 align:middle line:84%
He said, Thomas
pulled the gun out.

00:16:20.403 --> 00:16:22.300 align:middle line:84%
And he held his hand
like this and goes,

00:16:22.300 --> 00:16:24.610 align:middle line:84%
and he was popping
him like this.

00:16:24.610 --> 00:16:27.210 align:middle line:84%
He says, you should have seen
him hopping like a rabbit.

00:16:27.210 --> 00:16:28.330 align:middle line:90%
And was laughing.

00:16:28.330 --> 00:16:30.720 align:middle line:84%
He was enjoying the moment,
explaining this to me, right?

00:16:30.720 --> 00:16:31.510 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Wow.

00:16:31.510 --> 00:16:34.660 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: So I know
now I'm in thick.

00:16:34.660 --> 00:16:37.480 align:middle line:90%
And he's explaining this to me.

00:16:37.480 --> 00:16:39.910 align:middle line:84%
Well, Greg's kind of
disturbed about this.

00:16:39.910 --> 00:16:41.040 align:middle line:90%
And he leaves.

00:16:41.040 --> 00:16:42.770 align:middle line:90%
I get up to leave.

00:16:42.770 --> 00:16:45.400 align:middle line:84%
And as I'm leaving,
he grabs my shirt

00:16:45.400 --> 00:16:47.740 align:middle line:90%
one more time by the door.

00:16:47.740 --> 00:16:50.760 align:middle line:84%
He says if I tell anybody,
he's going to kill me.

00:16:50.760 --> 00:16:52.490 align:middle line:90%
And he shoves me out.

00:16:52.490 --> 00:16:56.317 align:middle line:84%
Well, I immediately go home,
and I call the detectives

00:16:56.317 --> 00:16:57.150 align:middle line:90%
in the police force.

00:16:57.150 --> 00:17:00.210 align:middle line:84%
And they said, Rob, you have
to go back, wear a wire,

00:17:00.210 --> 00:17:01.640 align:middle line:90%
and befriend him again.

00:17:01.640 --> 00:17:03.630 align:middle line:90%
And I said, there's no way.

00:17:03.630 --> 00:17:07.089 align:middle line:84%
Because he made me-- and there's
no way I'm gonna do this.

00:17:07.089 --> 00:17:07.810 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:17:07.810 --> 00:17:12.450 align:middle line:84%
So he told me he'd get off on
a technicality and an alibi.

00:17:12.450 --> 00:17:17.140 align:middle line:84%
And the prerequisite
of that was he

00:17:17.140 --> 00:17:19.990 align:middle line:84%
did have an alibi from
people out of town,

00:17:19.990 --> 00:17:21.589 align:middle line:90%
and there was a technicality.

00:17:21.589 --> 00:17:25.569 align:middle line:84%
But I knew right where
he ran and the place

00:17:25.569 --> 00:17:27.730 align:middle line:90%
that he took off to, and yeah.

00:17:27.730 --> 00:17:30.122 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's kind of a
rough entry into all of it.

00:17:30.122 --> 00:17:32.559 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Into the very first
of doing everything, sitting

00:17:32.559 --> 00:17:33.850 align:middle line:90%
two feet from a murderer, yeah.

00:17:33.850 --> 00:17:38.040 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so a few
questions arise from that.

00:17:38.040 --> 00:17:39.970 align:middle line:84%
One of them is,
wasn't that a little

00:17:39.970 --> 00:17:42.785 align:middle line:84%
disheartening to you that
you knew this, you saw this,

00:17:42.785 --> 00:17:44.160 align:middle line:84%
the guy was telling
you about it,

00:17:44.160 --> 00:17:45.745 align:middle line:84%
yet he gets off
on a technicality?

00:17:45.745 --> 00:17:46.370 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah.

00:17:46.370 --> 00:17:48.121 align:middle line:84%
It ate me, because I
wanted to be-- again,

00:17:48.121 --> 00:17:49.661 align:middle line:84%
going back to being
a police officer,

00:17:49.661 --> 00:17:51.020 align:middle line:90%
wanting to do the right thing.

00:17:51.020 --> 00:17:54.710 align:middle line:84%
It ate me so much
that a gym where

00:17:54.710 --> 00:17:58.630 align:middle line:84%
used to work out, his
brother used to work there,

00:17:58.630 --> 00:18:01.022 align:middle line:84%
and he would come
over, and he knew

00:18:01.022 --> 00:18:02.230 align:middle line:90%
that I was on to his brother.

00:18:02.230 --> 00:18:04.688 align:middle line:84%
And he would talk, and I said,
you know, one your brother's

00:18:04.688 --> 00:18:05.370 align:middle line:90%
going to get it.

00:18:05.370 --> 00:18:07.314 align:middle line:84%
And so he'd be not
too kind to me,

00:18:07.314 --> 00:18:08.480 align:middle line:90%
and I'm not too kind to him.

00:18:08.480 --> 00:18:10.850 align:middle line:84%
But it's that aspect
because I know.

00:18:10.850 --> 00:18:12.980 align:middle line:90%
I knew what was going on.

00:18:12.980 --> 00:18:14.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: What
happened to the man?

00:18:14.820 --> 00:18:15.320 align:middle line:90%
Jesse.

00:18:15.320 --> 00:18:19.230 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Well, Jesse is out
West, apparently, in Canada.

00:18:19.230 --> 00:18:23.070 align:middle line:84%
Thomas Cook re-murdered,
unfortunately.

00:18:23.070 --> 00:18:24.930 align:middle line:90%
Karma is karma.

00:18:24.930 --> 00:18:26.550 align:middle line:84%
But unfortunately,
a beautiful woman

00:18:26.550 --> 00:18:30.290 align:middle line:84%
had to die because
of some monster.

00:18:30.290 --> 00:18:31.791 align:middle line:84%
He saran wrapped
her, and he watched

00:18:31.791 --> 00:18:33.748 align:middle line:84%
her take her last breath--
because she couldn't

00:18:33.748 --> 00:18:35.230 align:middle line:90%
breathe-- in front of him.

00:18:35.230 --> 00:18:37.506 align:middle line:84%
And so now he's
in jail for life.

00:18:37.506 --> 00:18:39.380 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, at least
he's off the street.

00:18:39.380 --> 00:18:44.656 align:middle line:84%
And so before we get
into cases and such,

00:18:44.656 --> 00:18:46.530 align:middle line:84%
having been around these
people, as you said,

00:18:46.530 --> 00:18:50.720 align:middle line:84%
you see around some people that
really just are sociopathic.

00:18:50.720 --> 00:18:54.030 align:middle line:84%
They don't have any kind
of empathy for humanity.

00:18:54.030 --> 00:18:55.940 align:middle line:90%
You might see a black aura.

00:18:55.940 --> 00:18:58.720 align:middle line:84%
What else do you see
with people that we

00:18:58.720 --> 00:19:03.750 align:middle line:84%
consider to be the
toughest cases in society?

00:19:03.750 --> 00:19:09.090 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: When you lie-- a
case in Kentucky, two gentlemen

00:19:09.090 --> 00:19:13.800 align:middle line:84%
were murdered, there's
three parties to this

00:19:13.800 --> 00:19:16.480 align:middle line:84%
and a fourth on
the outside of it.

00:19:16.480 --> 00:19:20.180 align:middle line:84%
Since then-- again,
karma is karma.

00:19:20.180 --> 00:19:22.650 align:middle line:84%
A lot of them have
been killing themselves

00:19:22.650 --> 00:19:24.800 align:middle line:84%
because they live with
the karma, apparently.

00:19:24.800 --> 00:19:27.210 align:middle line:84%
One individual left on this
case, but the rest of them

00:19:27.210 --> 00:19:32.040 align:middle line:84%
are all dead-- I keep in
touch with every family,

00:19:32.040 --> 00:19:34.260 align:middle line:84%
so I know what's
going on in that area.

00:19:34.260 --> 00:19:36.722 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So suicide
is not uncommon

00:19:36.722 --> 00:19:38.180 align:middle line:84%
because they've
been so devastated.

00:19:38.180 --> 00:19:40.180 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Their demons get them.

00:19:40.180 --> 00:19:41.010 align:middle line:90%
They do.

00:19:41.010 --> 00:19:42.080 align:middle line:90%
They do.

00:19:42.080 --> 00:19:45.970 align:middle line:84%
I profiled this individual,
the detective Andy Delay.

00:19:45.970 --> 00:19:48.010 align:middle line:84%
He's in Clearwater,
Florida, now.

00:19:48.010 --> 00:19:50.220 align:middle line:84%
And we've got some
cases we're going

00:19:50.220 --> 00:19:53.850 align:middle line:84%
to be doing down there
with the Sheriff's office.

00:19:53.850 --> 00:19:56.150 align:middle line:90%
He was on this case with me.

00:19:56.150 --> 00:20:01.440 align:middle line:84%
Now, we were in the
hotel meeting room.

00:20:01.440 --> 00:20:03.750 align:middle line:84%
And they said, we have to
bring this one individual.

00:20:03.750 --> 00:20:04.870 align:middle line:90%
He's our key factor.

00:20:04.870 --> 00:20:07.620 align:middle line:84%
We have to present this
to him in order for him

00:20:07.620 --> 00:20:11.070 align:middle line:90%
to be a viable witness as well.

00:20:11.070 --> 00:20:14.930 align:middle line:84%
So I profiled his good side, his
bad side, and what he did it.

00:20:14.930 --> 00:20:17.580 align:middle line:90%
And we put it on Bristol Board.

00:20:17.580 --> 00:20:18.290 align:middle line:90%
We drove over.

00:20:18.290 --> 00:20:20.700 align:middle line:84%
He agreed to meet us at
the end of his driveway.

00:20:20.700 --> 00:20:21.640 align:middle line:90%
He did.

00:20:21.640 --> 00:20:22.980 align:middle line:90%
We bring out the tape recorder.

00:20:22.980 --> 00:20:25.240 align:middle line:90%
I'm holding the tape recorder.

00:20:25.240 --> 00:20:29.760 align:middle line:84%
And he's talking to a good
cop-- our good cop, bad cop,

00:20:29.760 --> 00:20:32.220 align:middle line:90%
doing that scenario.

00:20:32.220 --> 00:20:36.650 align:middle line:84%
And he addresses all these
issues with him very toughly.

00:20:36.650 --> 00:20:37.540 align:middle line:90%
He didn't like it.

00:20:37.540 --> 00:20:38.390 align:middle line:90%
So I take over.

00:20:38.390 --> 00:20:40.790 align:middle line:84%
I started explaining
certain things to him.

00:20:40.790 --> 00:20:41.715 align:middle line:90%
And I said, I see you.

00:20:41.715 --> 00:20:42.670 align:middle line:90%
I know where you were.

00:20:42.670 --> 00:20:44.180 align:middle line:84%
I know what happened,
how the fire was set,

00:20:44.180 --> 00:20:46.554 align:middle line:84%
how you trapped him in there,
how you cut their arms, how

00:20:46.554 --> 00:20:50.337 align:middle line:84%
you cut parts and you hit
them, the whole nine yards.

00:20:50.337 --> 00:20:51.670 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to get too graphic.

00:20:51.670 --> 00:20:54.960 align:middle line:84%
And he's like this, like
you, shaking his head,

00:20:54.960 --> 00:20:56.150 align:middle line:90%
shaking his head.

00:20:56.150 --> 00:20:59.700 align:middle line:84%
So I want the verbal so
I can get it on tape.

00:20:59.700 --> 00:21:01.180 align:middle line:90%
So I continue on.

00:21:01.180 --> 00:21:03.800 align:middle line:84%
Andy gets upset, pulls
the Bristol board out.

00:21:03.800 --> 00:21:06.430 align:middle line:84%
This boy couldn't believe
what was on the Bristol board.

00:21:06.430 --> 00:21:10.120 align:middle line:84%
And after seeing that, Andy
going through the points,

00:21:10.120 --> 00:21:12.530 align:middle line:84%
and them me talking to
him, he said, yes, yes.

00:21:12.530 --> 00:21:14.030 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that's
because you had

00:21:14.030 --> 00:21:15.710 align:middle line:90%
been able to see these things?

00:21:15.710 --> 00:21:16.659 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yes.

00:21:16.659 --> 00:21:18.950 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, now I want to
talk about the seeing part.

00:21:18.950 --> 00:21:19.900 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Absolutely.

00:21:19.900 --> 00:21:22.980 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So it comes to
you in a number of ways.

00:21:22.980 --> 00:21:24.530 align:middle line:84%
And as you say,
you work-- and we

00:21:24.530 --> 00:21:27.690 align:middle line:84%
were joking about the beams that
surround you here in studio.

00:21:27.690 --> 00:21:31.460 align:middle line:84%
A lot of them have a
good sense of humor.

00:21:31.460 --> 00:21:33.270 align:middle line:84%
You have beings
that you're working

00:21:33.270 --> 00:21:36.400 align:middle line:84%
with that are assisting you
and showing you what you need,

00:21:36.400 --> 00:21:37.850 align:middle line:90%
and your higher self.

00:21:37.850 --> 00:21:42.600 align:middle line:84%
But sometimes the actual
victim comes to you, too.

00:21:42.600 --> 00:21:48.560 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Yeah, and our
spirit is multi-dimensional.

00:21:48.560 --> 00:21:51.900 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people say and then
think this-- it stays within.

00:21:51.900 --> 00:21:56.370 align:middle line:84%
But our spirit is more
than that, all right?

00:21:56.370 --> 00:21:57.340 align:middle line:90%
Many realms.

00:21:57.340 --> 00:22:01.110 align:middle line:90%
And we encounter all of it.

00:22:01.110 --> 00:22:04.430 align:middle line:84%
Caesar Ivan Cano, a young
boy-- all I was given

00:22:04.430 --> 00:22:05.810 align:middle line:90%
was a photograph.

00:22:05.810 --> 00:22:07.750 align:middle line:84%
And I'm in Canada,
and he's murdered

00:22:07.750 --> 00:22:10.360 align:middle line:90%
in Louisville, Kentucky.

00:22:10.360 --> 00:22:11.550 align:middle line:90%
He's missing.

00:22:11.550 --> 00:22:12.800 align:middle line:90%
Can you please help?

00:22:12.800 --> 00:22:13.870 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:22:13.870 --> 00:22:15.540 align:middle line:90%
So they sent me a picture.

00:22:15.540 --> 00:22:18.110 align:middle line:90%
All I got was his name, Caesar.

00:22:18.110 --> 00:22:20.800 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking, and I'm
begging for information.

00:22:20.800 --> 00:22:24.095 align:middle line:84%
So I'm trying to
tap into my guides.

00:22:24.095 --> 00:22:26.150 align:middle line:84%
And I prayed to
God, and I prayed

00:22:26.150 --> 00:22:31.110 align:middle line:84%
to my family, who can help
me, and my guides and angels.

00:22:31.110 --> 00:22:33.250 align:middle line:84%
I start to get
certain information.

00:22:33.250 --> 00:22:37.520 align:middle line:84%
And I'm writing it down--
repeat offender, two boys.

00:22:37.520 --> 00:22:39.740 align:middle line:90%
So I write that down.

00:22:39.740 --> 00:22:44.930 align:middle line:84%
Then I start to ask his spirit
belonging team, spirit guides,

00:22:44.930 --> 00:22:47.090 align:middle line:90%
everything ties to him.

00:22:47.090 --> 00:22:49.799 align:middle line:84%
Stadium lights, like off--
and all this is on my website.

00:22:49.799 --> 00:22:51.340 align:middle line:84%
You can see my
automatic hand drawing

00:22:51.340 --> 00:22:52.402 align:middle line:90%
on my website about this.

00:22:52.402 --> 00:22:54.110 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, we
could see the pictures.

00:22:54.110 --> 00:22:59.710 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: So I draw the four
stadium lights, like off.

00:22:59.710 --> 00:23:03.462 align:middle line:84%
And apparently that night, they
were off when he went missing.

00:23:03.462 --> 00:23:04.920 align:middle line:84%
So there's the four
stadium lights.

00:23:04.920 --> 00:23:06.090 align:middle line:90%
I said, give me a name.

00:23:06.090 --> 00:23:06.770 align:middle line:90%
John.

00:23:06.770 --> 00:23:09.175 align:middle line:84%
So by the stadium
lights, I put John.

00:23:09.175 --> 00:23:12.350 align:middle line:84%
Now, if you stood on the
porch of the murderer's home

00:23:12.350 --> 00:23:14.930 align:middle line:84%
and you looked directly
through the little clearing,

00:23:14.930 --> 00:23:17.860 align:middle line:84%
Papa John Stadium
is right there.

00:23:17.860 --> 00:23:20.880 align:middle line:90%
So I ask, I need more.

00:23:20.880 --> 00:23:22.450 align:middle line:90%
Where exactly are you?

00:23:22.450 --> 00:23:25.004 align:middle line:84%
And I see construction,
orange vests.

00:23:25.004 --> 00:23:26.420 align:middle line:84%
They were doing
construction right

00:23:26.420 --> 00:23:29.510 align:middle line:90%
in front of the murderer's home.

00:23:29.510 --> 00:23:33.320 align:middle line:84%
And they had the flags, and
they wore the orange vests.

00:23:33.320 --> 00:23:38.010 align:middle line:84%
Apparently Caesar was playing
with the flags, pulling them

00:23:38.010 --> 00:23:41.500 align:middle line:84%
out, ended up in his home,
and that's what happened.

00:23:41.500 --> 00:23:43.900 align:middle line:84%
And we'll get to that
point in a minute.

00:23:43.900 --> 00:23:45.320 align:middle line:90%
I continue on.

00:23:45.320 --> 00:23:47.970 align:middle line:90%
And I say, and show me him.

00:23:47.970 --> 00:23:51.060 align:middle line:84%
So I'm drawing this out of
a four-year-old mindset.

00:23:51.060 --> 00:23:53.295 align:middle line:84%
It's really hard
to draw a picture--

00:23:53.295 --> 00:23:55.670 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because the little
boy is trying to relay this.

00:23:55.670 --> 00:23:57.870 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Exactly.

00:23:57.870 --> 00:23:59.115 align:middle line:90%
I can see here and draw you.

00:23:59.115 --> 00:24:00.115 align:middle line:90%
It would be picturesque.

00:24:00.115 --> 00:24:02.240 align:middle line:90%
It would be a beautiful picture.

00:24:02.240 --> 00:24:05.380 align:middle line:84%
But going to him out of
his flashing through me,

00:24:05.380 --> 00:24:07.470 align:middle line:84%
I'm seeing the man
with the pointy ears,

00:24:07.470 --> 00:24:10.090 align:middle line:84%
and I'm drawing as fast as I
can, because other information

00:24:10.090 --> 00:24:11.490 align:middle line:90%
is coming in.

00:24:11.490 --> 00:24:13.550 align:middle line:90%
And then there's a break.

00:24:13.550 --> 00:24:15.370 align:middle line:90%
And then I felt the pull-away.

00:24:15.370 --> 00:24:20.770 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I knew that
this was him being murdered.

00:24:20.770 --> 00:24:22.060 align:middle line:90%
So I'm upset.

00:24:22.060 --> 00:24:24.340 align:middle line:84%
There's about maybe
5, 10 minutes go by.

00:24:24.340 --> 00:24:25.900 align:middle line:90%
And there's nothing.

00:24:25.900 --> 00:24:27.130 align:middle line:90%
And I'm upset.

00:24:27.130 --> 00:24:30.570 align:middle line:84%
I'm pacing my office, and I'm
going back, and I'm asking,

00:24:30.570 --> 00:24:31.640 align:middle line:90%
what's going on?

00:24:31.640 --> 00:24:34.370 align:middle line:84%
And then all of a sudden,
I'm back in again.

00:24:34.370 --> 00:24:36.280 align:middle line:90%
And now I'm getting it from him.

00:24:36.280 --> 00:24:37.830 align:middle line:90%
I said, give me his name.

00:24:37.830 --> 00:24:38.790 align:middle line:90%
And he did.

00:24:38.790 --> 00:24:40.310 align:middle line:90%
He gave me Cecil.

00:24:40.310 --> 00:24:42.560 align:middle line:90%
It's not a Bob, John, or a Mary.

00:24:42.560 --> 00:24:43.720 align:middle line:90%
It's a Cecil.

00:24:43.720 --> 00:24:46.810 align:middle line:84%
And I write "Cecil," and
I put an arrow right down

00:24:46.810 --> 00:24:50.720 align:middle line:84%
to the monster's head
that he made me draw.

00:24:50.720 --> 00:24:53.140 align:middle line:84%
So then I continue on, and
there's some other information.

00:24:53.140 --> 00:24:55.690 align:middle line:90%


00:24:55.690 --> 00:25:01.250 align:middle line:84%
What ended up was poor
Caesar-- I get choked up.

00:25:01.250 --> 00:25:05.323 align:middle line:84%
Poor Caesar was
drowned in his bathtub.

00:25:05.323 --> 00:25:06.390 align:middle line:90%
And he held him down.

00:25:06.390 --> 00:25:09.280 align:middle line:90%


00:25:09.280 --> 00:25:12.100 align:middle line:90%
It's hard when it's a child.

00:25:12.100 --> 00:25:14.830 align:middle line:90%
Because I got children.

00:25:14.830 --> 00:25:17.290 align:middle line:90%
We love our children.

00:25:17.290 --> 00:25:20.070 align:middle line:90%
And any mom-- and his poor mom.

00:25:20.070 --> 00:25:25.506 align:middle line:84%
I mean, she was the only
one raising him, single mom.

00:25:25.506 --> 00:25:26.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's devastating.

00:25:26.630 --> 00:25:27.825 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yup, yup.

00:25:27.825 --> 00:25:30.740 align:middle line:84%
And so I got all
this information,

00:25:30.740 --> 00:25:34.490 align:middle line:84%
and come to learn afterwards, he
was a repeat offender sexually

00:25:34.490 --> 00:25:36.130 align:middle line:90%
of two young boys.

00:25:36.130 --> 00:25:37.870 align:middle line:84%
So that goes back
to tie in to that.

00:25:37.870 --> 00:25:40.710 align:middle line:90%


00:25:40.710 --> 00:25:43.300 align:middle line:84%
Information went back and forth
in emails between investigator

00:25:43.300 --> 00:25:46.060 align:middle line:84%
in Louisville, Kentucky,
going to the detective

00:25:46.060 --> 00:25:48.425 align:middle line:90%
on the case and myself.

00:25:48.425 --> 00:25:51.270 align:middle line:84%
And I keep every
notation of every case

00:25:51.270 --> 00:25:52.900 align:middle line:90%
I do, emails and what have you.

