It went to the news agency,
John Boel, I think it was,

00:25:56.380 --> 00:25:58.500 align:middle line:90%
in Louisville.

00:25:58.500 --> 00:26:01.070 align:middle line:84%
So everybody had a piece of
what was really happening

00:26:01.070 --> 00:26:05.730 align:middle line:84%
momentarily, like right
away from my office.

00:26:05.730 --> 00:26:08.180 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes I still-- and
it's been that long,

00:26:08.180 --> 00:26:11.310 align:middle line:84%
and I still wake up--
what if, what if?

00:26:11.310 --> 00:26:13.570 align:middle line:84%
What if I would have
done it differently?

00:26:13.570 --> 00:26:16.060 align:middle line:84%
But you can't stop
the inevitable.

00:26:16.060 --> 00:26:18.030 align:middle line:90%
I've learned that through God.

00:26:18.030 --> 00:26:19.960 align:middle line:90%
You can't stop the inevitable.

00:26:19.960 --> 00:26:21.310 align:middle line:90%
You grow from it.

00:26:21.310 --> 00:26:22.630 align:middle line:90%
You mature from it.

00:26:22.630 --> 00:26:26.630 align:middle line:84%
And it helps you in
life to progress.

00:26:26.630 --> 00:26:28.970 align:middle line:84%
Being this deep into
cases like that,

00:26:28.970 --> 00:26:33.930 align:middle line:84%
people wonder how
I want to do this.

00:26:33.930 --> 00:26:36.410 align:middle line:84%
I get a lot of letters from
people, I want to do this.

00:26:36.410 --> 00:26:37.190 align:middle line:90%
No, you don't.

00:26:37.190 --> 00:26:37.830 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:26:37.830 --> 00:26:38.990 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: You don't.

00:26:38.990 --> 00:26:41.346 align:middle line:90%
Just be you.

00:26:41.346 --> 00:26:42.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, how
do people find you?

00:26:42.970 --> 00:26:45.250 align:middle line:84%
I mean, obviously there's
a criminal element,

00:26:45.250 --> 00:26:47.460 align:middle line:84%
and the normal
agencies are involved

00:26:47.460 --> 00:26:51.490 align:middle line:84%
when someone has gone missing
or someone has been killed.

00:26:51.490 --> 00:26:54.170 align:middle line:84%
And how do you come
into the picture?

00:26:54.170 --> 00:26:56.670 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: A case I'm doing right
now-- there's many of them,

00:26:56.670 --> 00:26:59.430 align:middle line:90%
but there's a case right now.

00:26:59.430 --> 00:27:02.920 align:middle line:84%
A mother had custody, just
won custody of her child.

00:27:02.920 --> 00:27:05.093 align:middle line:84%
This is in-- I'm trying
to think of the state.

00:27:05.093 --> 00:27:07.270 align:middle line:90%
It's Washington-- Seattle.

00:27:07.270 --> 00:27:09.450 align:middle line:84%
I'm working with the
detective on that.

00:27:09.450 --> 00:27:12.035 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: So they know of you?

00:27:12.035 --> 00:27:12.660 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah.

00:27:12.660 --> 00:27:13.600 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean,
a lot of people

00:27:13.600 --> 00:27:15.220 align:middle line:90%
know of you by now, obviously.

00:27:15.220 --> 00:27:17.210 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: It's like a 50-50 mix.

00:27:17.210 --> 00:27:19.560 align:middle line:84%
I'll get the police
contact me, or they'll

00:27:19.560 --> 00:27:22.960 align:middle line:84%
have the family member, like
yourself, contact me, say,

00:27:22.960 --> 00:27:24.407 align:middle line:84%
can you put him
in touch with us?

00:27:24.407 --> 00:27:25.240 align:middle line:90%
And they'll do that.

00:27:25.240 --> 00:27:26.580 align:middle line:90%
Or they'll know of me.

00:27:26.580 --> 00:27:29.540 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So the
police are pretty open?

00:27:29.540 --> 00:27:32.430 align:middle line:84%
They're open to using
your types of abilities?

00:27:32.430 --> 00:27:33.680 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: There are some, yes.

00:27:33.680 --> 00:27:34.720 align:middle line:90%
And some are skeptics still.

00:27:34.720 --> 00:27:35.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I was going
to say, some must still

00:27:35.820 --> 00:27:37.560 align:middle line:84%
have some of the macho
thing, like, hey, there's

00:27:37.560 --> 00:27:38.290 align:middle line:90%
a way to do this.

00:27:38.290 --> 00:27:38.980 align:middle line:90%
Get out of my way.

00:27:38.980 --> 00:27:39.920 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Yeah, and
I don't blame them.

00:27:39.920 --> 00:27:41.670 align:middle line:84%
Because, you know,
there's a lot out there

00:27:41.670 --> 00:27:43.030 align:middle line:90%
that's going on that's wrong.

00:27:43.030 --> 00:27:44.330 align:middle line:90%
And I don't blame them.

00:27:44.330 --> 00:27:48.560 align:middle line:84%
Case out of Boston--
a friend of mine,

00:27:48.560 --> 00:27:50.160 align:middle line:90%
he works with the DOE Network.

00:27:50.160 --> 00:27:52.320 align:middle line:84%
And his brother's
daughter was murdered.

00:27:52.320 --> 00:27:53.910 align:middle line:84%
So he asked me,
and I said, sure.

00:27:53.910 --> 00:27:55.993 align:middle line:84%
He said, I'll put you in
touch with the detective.

00:27:55.993 --> 00:27:58.480 align:middle line:90%
So I said, OK, fine.

00:27:58.480 --> 00:28:01.390 align:middle line:84%
I ain't telling you nothing, and
Tommy's straight-nosed, right?

00:28:01.390 --> 00:28:02.180 align:middle line:90%
I ain't telling you nothing.

00:28:02.180 --> 00:28:04.179 align:middle line:84%
I'll just give you a
picture like you always do.

00:28:04.179 --> 00:28:04.840 align:middle line:90%
So fine.

00:28:04.840 --> 00:28:06.360 align:middle line:84%
So he gives me a
picture, puts me

00:28:06.360 --> 00:28:08.100 align:middle line:84%
in touch with
Detective Morissette.

00:28:08.100 --> 00:28:09.430 align:middle line:90%
I do my drawings.

00:28:09.430 --> 00:28:11.230 align:middle line:90%
I do all my information.

00:28:11.230 --> 00:28:14.360 align:middle line:84%
And I talked to the detective
before I fax it to him.

00:28:14.360 --> 00:28:15.820 align:middle line:90%
He goes, well, you know what?

00:28:15.820 --> 00:28:16.910 align:middle line:90%
And this is true.

00:28:16.910 --> 00:28:18.970 align:middle line:84%
This is how they
speak to anybody.

00:28:18.970 --> 00:28:23.070 align:middle line:84%
If anything touches this
case, I'll contact you back.

00:28:23.070 --> 00:28:24.670 align:middle line:90%
If not, don't worry about it.

00:28:24.670 --> 00:28:27.160 align:middle line:84%
So it's like a brush-off,
Dear John type thing.

00:28:27.160 --> 00:28:28.617 align:middle line:90%
So I understand.

00:28:28.617 --> 00:28:30.950 align:middle line:84%
And that's a great way to do
it, because they can't just

00:28:30.950 --> 00:28:33.970 align:middle line:84%
approach everybody and take
it for the sake of taking

00:28:33.970 --> 00:28:35.970 align:middle line:90%
information, saying, this is it.

00:28:35.970 --> 00:28:39.405 align:middle line:90%
So I sent it to him.

00:28:39.405 --> 00:28:40.280 align:middle line:90%
And I'm sitting down.

00:28:40.280 --> 00:28:42.275 align:middle line:84%
The phone rang about
five minutes later.

00:28:42.275 --> 00:28:45.330 align:middle line:84%
And he's going, how much
information did they tell you?

00:28:45.330 --> 00:28:46.770 align:middle line:90%
I need you to tell me the truth.

00:28:46.770 --> 00:28:48.395 align:middle line:84%
And said, they didn't
tell me anything.

00:28:48.395 --> 00:28:49.790 align:middle line:90%
They just gave me a picture.

00:28:49.790 --> 00:28:52.560 align:middle line:84%
And they go, we have
that guy in jail now.

00:28:52.560 --> 00:28:55.677 align:middle line:84%
So, yeah, it was amazing all
the stuff that tied to him.

00:28:55.677 --> 00:28:57.260 align:middle line:84%
And they were trying
to tie it to him.

00:28:57.260 --> 00:29:02.770 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately, and I
promised Tommy and his brother

00:29:02.770 --> 00:29:04.550 align:middle line:84%
that we would have
this completely solved

00:29:04.550 --> 00:29:07.324 align:middle line:84%
before his brother-- his brother
ended up dying of cancer.

00:29:07.324 --> 00:29:07.865 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh.

00:29:07.865 --> 00:29:09.240 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah, I know.

00:29:09.240 --> 00:29:10.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: He didn't
have that satisfaction.

00:29:10.240 --> 00:29:10.570 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: I never give up.

00:29:10.570 --> 00:29:11.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: But it doesn't matter.

00:29:11.780 --> 00:29:12.290 align:middle line:90%
On some level--

00:29:12.290 --> 00:29:13.248 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: He knows now.

00:29:13.248 --> 00:29:14.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: He knows now, exactly.

00:29:14.910 --> 00:29:16.830 align:middle line:90%
And you're paying attention.

00:29:16.830 --> 00:29:19.174 align:middle line:84%
OK, so before we go on to
some of the other cases,

00:29:19.174 --> 00:29:21.090 align:middle line:84%
I want to go back to
Seattle in a minute, too.

00:29:21.090 --> 00:29:26.340 align:middle line:84%
But most people know about
this through pop culture

00:29:26.340 --> 00:29:29.050 align:middle line:84%
or shows like "Medium,"
Allison DuBois.

00:29:29.050 --> 00:29:31.870 align:middle line:90%


00:29:31.870 --> 00:29:38.610 align:middle line:84%
OK, so let's talk about the
reality of that versus what

00:29:38.610 --> 00:29:41.430 align:middle line:90%
we're shown on television, OK?

00:29:41.430 --> 00:29:43.066 align:middle line:84%
I know your face
just went funny.

00:29:43.066 --> 00:29:43.690 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah.

00:29:43.690 --> 00:29:45.596 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's talk
about the "Medium."

00:29:45.596 --> 00:29:46.137 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: OK.

00:29:46.137 --> 00:29:50.920 align:middle line:90%


00:29:50.920 --> 00:29:53.180 align:middle line:84%
I have another show
that's in production.

00:29:53.180 --> 00:29:58.410 align:middle line:10%
And it's called "The Bar's
Open with Robbie Thomas."

00:29:58.410 --> 00:29:59.950 align:middle line:90%
It's not just a bar to drink.

00:29:59.950 --> 00:30:05.360 align:middle line:84%
It's a bar where we discuss
the cases, how I feel,

00:30:05.360 --> 00:30:09.050 align:middle line:84%
what's real with somebody
like myself doing what I do.

00:30:09.050 --> 00:30:14.220 align:middle line:84%
Do I just go home, watch
TV, and eat hot dogs?

00:30:14.220 --> 00:30:19.210 align:middle line:84%
Or do psychics really go
and paint their nails?

00:30:19.210 --> 00:30:23.160 align:middle line:84%
So we want to give the real
gist of what really happens.

00:30:23.160 --> 00:30:25.180 align:middle line:90%
We use that word "unnerving."

00:30:25.180 --> 00:30:28.290 align:middle line:84%
It's unnerving because what
happens is I do a case,

00:30:28.290 --> 00:30:30.010 align:middle line:90%
I don't stop.

00:30:30.010 --> 00:30:31.590 align:middle line:90%
It affects my whole life.

00:30:31.590 --> 00:30:33.120 align:middle line:84%
Thank God for my
wife, because she's

00:30:33.120 --> 00:30:35.610 align:middle line:84%
like the core and the
backbone of who I am.

00:30:35.610 --> 00:30:38.515 align:middle line:84%
My children know that
I've taken on cases that

00:30:38.515 --> 00:30:40.640 align:middle line:90%
aren't dangers, and my wife.

00:30:40.640 --> 00:30:42.390 align:middle line:84%
And we'll touch upon
that other case.

00:30:42.390 --> 00:30:43.860 align:middle line:84%
There's many we
could talk about.

00:30:43.860 --> 00:30:48.324 align:middle line:90%
But yeah, I need that structure.

00:30:48.324 --> 00:30:49.865 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Family is
what grounds you.

00:30:49.865 --> 00:30:50.790 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Yeah, it
grounds me big time.

00:30:50.790 --> 00:30:51.880 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And it's all females.

00:30:51.880 --> 00:30:52.350 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah.

00:30:52.350 --> 00:30:54.600 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You've got a bunch
of-- a slew of daughters.

00:30:54.600 --> 00:30:55.940 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yes.

00:30:55.940 --> 00:30:58.060 align:middle line:84%
You know, females
should run this world.

00:30:58.060 --> 00:30:58.585 align:middle line:90%
It's true.

00:30:58.585 --> 00:30:59.610 align:middle line:90%
It's true, really.

00:30:59.610 --> 00:31:00.610 align:middle line:90%
This guy ego stuff--

00:31:00.610 --> 00:31:02.520 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And yet most of the
perps that you're dealing with

00:31:02.520 --> 00:31:03.161 align:middle line:90%
are men.

00:31:03.161 --> 00:31:05.410 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it makes sense that
all the women in your life

00:31:05.410 --> 00:31:06.550 align:middle line:90%
would balance you back out.

00:31:06.550 --> 00:31:07.591 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Oh, absolutely.

00:31:07.591 --> 00:31:10.270 align:middle line:84%
Because you deal with the trash,
and you come home to the good,

00:31:10.270 --> 00:31:11.200 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:31:11.200 --> 00:31:16.899 align:middle line:84%
But I still reflect to
every case, and it hurts.

00:31:16.899 --> 00:31:18.440 align:middle line:84%
I wake up in the
middle of the night,

00:31:18.440 --> 00:31:19.710 align:middle line:90%
and I'll talk to my wife.

00:31:19.710 --> 00:31:20.970 align:middle line:90%
I'll discuss a case.

00:31:20.970 --> 00:31:22.060 align:middle line:90%
She'll listen to me.

00:31:22.060 --> 00:31:24.240 align:middle line:90%
And she'll say-- she grounds me.

00:31:24.240 --> 00:31:26.490 align:middle line:84%
And just whatever she
tells me directs me.

00:31:26.490 --> 00:31:28.720 align:middle line:90%
It's always right.

00:31:28.720 --> 00:31:29.800 align:middle line:90%
Then I ease off a bit.

00:31:29.800 --> 00:31:31.740 align:middle line:90%
Then I'm OK for a day or two.

00:31:31.740 --> 00:31:34.582 align:middle line:84%
Then there's another
case, and I talk about it.

00:31:34.582 --> 00:31:36.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So she's
you're sounding board,

00:31:36.290 --> 00:31:38.581 align:middle line:84%
and it sounds like she's
pretty intuitive and grounded.

00:31:38.581 --> 00:31:40.360 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Oh, absolutely she is.

00:31:40.360 --> 00:31:43.050 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, she knows what's going on.

00:31:43.050 --> 00:31:45.440 align:middle line:90%
She knows me.

00:31:45.440 --> 00:31:46.470 align:middle line:90%
It's true.

00:31:46.470 --> 00:31:48.070 align:middle line:90%
So it's good.

00:31:48.070 --> 00:31:50.170 align:middle line:90%
It's good.

00:31:50.170 --> 00:31:54.230 align:middle line:84%
But the good, the bad,
the ugly-- and she said,

00:31:54.230 --> 00:31:55.480 align:middle line:90%
you've got to talk about this.

00:31:55.480 --> 00:31:56.560 align:middle line:90%
And this is from her.

00:31:56.560 --> 00:31:59.100 align:middle line:84%
You have to talk about the
good, the bad, the ugly.

00:31:59.100 --> 00:32:01.260 align:middle line:84%
The good is yes,
we get reprieve,

00:32:01.260 --> 00:32:03.820 align:middle line:84%
we get solace sometimes,
and sometimes we

00:32:03.820 --> 00:32:07.360 align:middle line:84%
bring that little
help to the families,

00:32:07.360 --> 00:32:10.390 align:middle line:84%
even if it's not the
proper result in the end,

00:32:10.390 --> 00:32:12.122 align:middle line:90%
but they find out.

00:32:12.122 --> 00:32:13.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: The resolution.

00:32:13.300 --> 00:32:15.300 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: The resolution, right?

00:32:15.300 --> 00:32:18.800 align:middle line:84%
The bad about it is if you're
not helping a family enough--

00:32:18.800 --> 00:32:20.320 align:middle line:90%
and I've run into this.

00:32:20.320 --> 00:32:24.050 align:middle line:90%
And I'm not saying I'm perfect.

00:32:24.050 --> 00:32:27.590 align:middle line:84%
I run into it where if I
don't help them enough or if I

00:32:27.590 --> 00:32:33.290 align:middle line:84%
don't-- families want me to
be the counselor, the lawyer,

00:32:33.290 --> 00:32:35.540 align:middle line:84%
the police officer,
everything in between.

00:32:35.540 --> 00:32:37.090 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because they think
you can see everything,

00:32:37.090 --> 00:32:38.373 align:middle line:90%
and they want you to-- yeah.

00:32:38.373 --> 00:32:39.240 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah.

00:32:39.240 --> 00:32:40.660 align:middle line:90%
But I'm there to do a job.

00:32:40.660 --> 00:32:44.940 align:middle line:84%
And the job is to help you and
to make understanding of what's

00:32:44.940 --> 00:32:48.536 align:middle line:84%
going on so it leads
to this result.

00:32:48.536 --> 00:32:49.660 align:middle line:90%
But that's not good enough.

00:32:49.660 --> 00:32:55.960 align:middle line:84%
So then they get upset,
and things happen.

00:32:55.960 --> 00:32:59.040 align:middle line:84%
But that is perfectly OK,
because that is the family,

00:32:59.040 --> 00:33:00.910 align:middle line:90%
and you can't blame them.

00:33:00.910 --> 00:33:03.940 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they want their child
or their husband or their wife

00:33:03.940 --> 00:33:04.640 align:middle line:90%
back.

00:33:04.640 --> 00:33:07.050 align:middle line:84%
And the ugly part
about it is the fact

00:33:07.050 --> 00:33:11.730 align:middle line:84%
that you have all these
people who critique you

00:33:11.730 --> 00:33:16.610 align:middle line:84%
but they actually are not
on scene, death scene.

00:33:16.610 --> 00:33:19.731 align:middle line:84%
They're not sitting in office
with the detectives, with you.

00:33:19.731 --> 00:33:21.980 align:middle line:84%
They're not there where
you're giving the information.

00:33:21.980 --> 00:33:23.500 align:middle line:90%
But they know all.

00:33:23.500 --> 00:33:24.270 align:middle line:90%
They see all.

00:33:24.270 --> 00:33:32.610 align:middle line:84%
And you know, the skeptics,
and I'm not knocking atheists,

00:33:32.610 --> 00:33:34.790 align:middle line:84%
but there are radical
people out there

00:33:34.790 --> 00:33:36.790 align:middle line:84%
who want to just attack
you for no reason at all

00:33:36.790 --> 00:33:38.500 align:middle line:90%
because they think they know.

00:33:38.500 --> 00:33:42.650 align:middle line:84%
And that's fine, because
I'm a straight shooter.

00:33:42.650 --> 00:33:45.570 align:middle line:84%
I don't buy into what
they go or anybody--

00:33:45.570 --> 00:33:49.597 align:middle line:84%
as long as I know that the
family and I understand--

00:33:49.597 --> 00:33:50.930 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You've done your best.

00:33:50.930 --> 00:33:52.270 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: I've done my best.

00:33:52.270 --> 00:33:53.770 align:middle line:84%
And you see their
letters from them,

00:33:53.770 --> 00:33:57.400 align:middle line:84%
saying, thank you for bringing
my daughter home alive.

00:33:57.400 --> 00:34:00.290 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for helping us out.

00:34:00.290 --> 00:34:03.560 align:middle line:84%
We caught this guy who broke
into our home and stuff

00:34:03.560 --> 00:34:04.320 align:middle line:90%
like that.

00:34:04.320 --> 00:34:05.764 align:middle line:90%
That's the result we look for.

00:34:05.764 --> 00:34:06.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:34:06.430 --> 00:34:07.250 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: We'll
don't look for this.

00:34:07.250 --> 00:34:09.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But you
still get the skeptics.

00:34:09.080 --> 00:34:09.955 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Oh, you do.

00:34:09.955 --> 00:34:12.730 align:middle line:84%
And I've learned over the
years you just grow with it.

00:34:12.730 --> 00:34:13.469 align:middle line:90%
You do.

00:34:13.469 --> 00:34:15.110 align:middle line:84%
Because if I'm
occupying their time,

00:34:15.110 --> 00:34:16.830 align:middle line:90%
I'm doing something right.

00:34:16.830 --> 00:34:19.163 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so now we've
kind of beat around the bush.

00:34:19.163 --> 00:34:20.610 align:middle line:90%
Let's go back to Allison DuBois.

00:34:20.610 --> 00:34:22.250 align:middle line:90%
Let's go back to the "Medium."

00:34:22.250 --> 00:34:26.920 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: The "Medium"-- here's
the ugly of it, too, I call it,

00:34:26.920 --> 00:34:29.620 align:middle line:84%
and I put it in that sense, is
that there's so many people out

00:34:29.620 --> 00:34:32.409 align:middle line:90%
there giving disinformation.

00:34:32.409 --> 00:34:34.409 align:middle line:84%
They're not discerning
it properly.

00:34:34.409 --> 00:34:40.239 align:middle line:84%
And the misinformation they get
makes the police and families

00:34:40.239 --> 00:34:42.280 align:middle line:84%
look down on people who
are really actually doing

00:34:42.280 --> 00:34:46.030 align:middle line:84%
the job, who can go out
there and actually say,

00:34:46.030 --> 00:34:47.840 align:middle line:90%
the man's name is Cecil.

00:34:47.840 --> 00:34:51.439 align:middle line:84%
Or I can get your daughter
out of the sex slave trade,

00:34:51.439 --> 00:34:53.489 align:middle line:90%
and we do within three days.

00:34:53.489 --> 00:34:55.389 align:middle line:84%
That's what's the
ugly part about it.

00:34:55.389 --> 00:34:58.390 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So where has DuBois
and the "Medium" come in there?

00:34:58.390 --> 00:35:01.640 align:middle line:84%
Is it that maybe some of
that work wasn't exactly

00:35:01.640 --> 00:35:04.120 align:middle line:90%
the clearest reflection?

00:35:04.120 --> 00:35:06.154 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Looking
at the show, not

00:35:06.154 --> 00:35:07.570 align:middle line:84%
knocking Hollywood,
because we all

00:35:07.570 --> 00:35:11.330 align:middle line:84%
love Hollywood and
aspects of how we

00:35:11.330 --> 00:35:13.595 align:middle line:90%
have to drag out things on TV.

00:35:13.595 --> 00:35:16.510 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, it gave
credibility in a sense to you

00:35:16.510 --> 00:35:17.400 align:middle line:90%
and people like you.

00:35:17.400 --> 00:35:18.410 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Sure, or
other people who do--

00:35:18.410 --> 00:35:20.034 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And others
who do this, yeah.

00:35:20.034 --> 00:35:22.410 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah, absolutely.

00:35:22.410 --> 00:35:24.050 align:middle line:84%
You have to look
at what is real.

00:35:24.050 --> 00:35:26.760 align:middle line:90%


00:35:26.760 --> 00:35:30.990 align:middle line:84%
I don't go and-- as we've
seen on TV, and you look

00:35:30.990 --> 00:35:34.210 align:middle line:84%
and you see this and that--
they have to foreshadow things.

00:35:34.210 --> 00:35:36.910 align:middle line:84%
They have to make it
look like it's a resume,

00:35:36.910 --> 00:35:39.330 align:middle line:90%
and this is how it's done.

00:35:39.330 --> 00:35:42.360 align:middle line:90%
It's not done like that.

00:35:42.360 --> 00:35:46.770 align:middle line:84%
I'm on scene, and I know
two men have died there.

00:35:46.770 --> 00:35:48.400 align:middle line:84%
And I know they
cut their arms off.

00:35:48.400 --> 00:35:50.170 align:middle line:90%
And they gutted them like deers.

00:35:50.170 --> 00:35:55.250 align:middle line:84%
And they buried them inside
and burned them alive

00:35:55.250 --> 00:35:57.496 align:middle line:90%
while they were still alive.

00:35:57.496 --> 00:36:00.780 align:middle line:84%
And I'm seeing this, and
I'm telling the families.

00:36:00.780 --> 00:36:03.710 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's not a
"Medium" moment.

00:36:03.710 --> 00:36:07.575 align:middle line:84%
Or it's not a "Ghost Whisperer"
or any other type of show.

00:36:07.575 --> 00:36:09.700 align:middle line:84%
I'm not knocking those
shows, because this is good.

00:36:09.700 --> 00:36:11.574 align:middle line:84%
People have to learn,
and it's a good aspect.

00:36:11.574 --> 00:36:14.080 align:middle line:84%
But they're being driven
in the wrong direction

00:36:14.080 --> 00:36:15.630 align:middle line:90%
of how it really is.

00:36:15.630 --> 00:36:19.375 align:middle line:84%
Then you sit in office, and
you pour over information

00:36:19.375 --> 00:36:22.320 align:middle line:84%
that you write out in point
form or whatever I can give

00:36:22.320 --> 00:36:24.420 align:middle line:90%
to the police or the families.

00:36:24.420 --> 00:36:26.770 align:middle line:84%
And then they look at that,
and it's more tangible.

00:36:26.770 --> 00:36:29.930 align:middle line:84%
Because now they have something
to lead, to work with.

00:36:29.930 --> 00:36:32.970 align:middle line:84%
And that's how
they do their job.

00:36:32.970 --> 00:36:34.789 align:middle line:90%
It's not glorified.

00:36:34.789 --> 00:36:35.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:36:35.330 --> 00:36:37.700 align:middle line:84%
I mean, how long does
it take after something

00:36:37.700 --> 00:36:42.020 align:middle line:84%
as grizzly as, say, the
case you just mentioned.

00:36:42.020 --> 00:36:44.799 align:middle line:84%
How long does it take before
you can really kind of--

00:36:44.799 --> 00:36:45.590 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Download?

00:36:45.590 --> 00:36:48.670 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --dissipate all
that energy and those images

00:36:48.670 --> 00:36:51.281 align:middle line:90%
from your being?

00:36:51.281 --> 00:36:53.350 align:middle line:84%
It has to be a
little, I don't know,

00:36:53.350 --> 00:36:56.200 align:middle line:84%
disturbing just to have that
stuff mucking around in there?

00:36:56.200 --> 00:36:57.830 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: That's a good word.

00:36:57.830 --> 00:37:00.046 align:middle line:90%
It don't leave you.

00:37:00.046 --> 00:37:00.940 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It doesn't?

00:37:00.940 --> 00:37:01.648 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: No, no.

00:37:01.648 --> 00:37:03.340 align:middle line:90%
It don't dissipate.

00:37:03.340 --> 00:37:07.050 align:middle line:84%
It may get better over time
because you deal with it.

00:37:07.050 --> 00:37:09.080 align:middle line:90%
And then I know reality.

00:37:09.080 --> 00:37:10.710 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I sit down.

00:37:10.710 --> 00:37:12.940 align:middle line:84%
We watch TV, my
daughters, my wife.

00:37:12.940 --> 00:37:14.940 align:middle line:84%
And often my daughters
will ask questions,

00:37:14.940 --> 00:37:17.180 align:middle line:84%
was it like that
on that case, Dad?

00:37:17.180 --> 00:37:19.156 align:middle line:90%
So it just never leaves you.

00:37:19.156 --> 00:37:23.320 align:middle line:84%
You have the reality side
of it in questioning form.

00:37:23.320 --> 00:37:26.460 align:middle line:84%
You have your own
demons, if you will,

00:37:26.460 --> 00:37:29.530 align:middle line:84%
that hound you because
of what you've done.

00:37:29.530 --> 00:37:32.190 align:middle line:84%
And you look at the
police officers,

00:37:32.190 --> 00:37:34.720 align:middle line:84%
and they say, I can't
take it anymore,

00:37:34.720 --> 00:37:38.780 align:middle line:84%
or Post Traumatic
Stress Disorder.

00:37:38.780 --> 00:37:39.980 align:middle line:90%
And it's there.

00:37:39.980 --> 00:37:41.790 align:middle line:84%
People don't realize
it, but it's there.

00:37:41.790 --> 00:37:44.420 align:middle line:84%
They see these
things all the time.

00:37:44.420 --> 00:37:46.070 align:middle line:84%
And then I do that,
I still see it.

00:37:46.070 --> 00:37:48.630 align:middle line:84%
And so when I go through
it, I pray a lot.

00:37:48.630 --> 00:37:50.670 align:middle line:84%
I pray like a
million times a day.

00:37:50.670 --> 00:37:51.354 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, I have to.

00:37:51.354 --> 00:37:52.270 align:middle line:90%
That's my discernment.

00:37:52.270 --> 00:37:54.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, you're
very spiritually oriented.

00:37:54.080 --> 00:37:54.954 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Absolutely.

00:37:54.954 --> 00:37:55.610 align:middle line:90%
You have to.

00:37:55.610 --> 00:37:57.215 align:middle line:90%
That's my way out.

00:37:57.215 --> 00:37:59.590 align:middle line:84%
If I didn't have
that, I would think

00:37:59.590 --> 00:38:05.100 align:middle line:84%
I would be a little bit of a
recluse, reckless in my life,

00:38:05.100 --> 00:38:10.220 align:middle line:84%
a different tangible of a Robbie
than what should be for people.

00:38:10.220 --> 00:38:12.670 align:middle line:90%
So I'm people-oriented.

00:38:12.670 --> 00:38:13.740 align:middle line:90%
I know my focus.

00:38:13.740 --> 00:38:15.940 align:middle line:84%
And it's to continue
to do what I do.

00:38:15.940 --> 00:38:17.470 align:middle line:90%
And that gives me the strength.

00:38:17.470 --> 00:38:19.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, we
do a lot of shows

00:38:19.140 --> 00:38:23.170 align:middle line:84%
on people who deal with
multidimensional realms

00:38:23.170 --> 00:38:27.170 align:middle line:84%
and people who do angel
readings and all of this.

00:38:27.170 --> 00:38:30.560 align:middle line:84%
But we don't usually have
someone who is specifically

00:38:30.560 --> 00:38:34.960 align:middle line:84%
having, for the better good, to
muck around in the dark side.

00:38:34.960 --> 00:38:37.130 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: If I have
another choice--

00:38:37.130 --> 00:38:40.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But it sounds like you
were kind of called to do this.

00:38:40.100 --> 00:38:44.080 align:middle line:84%
And it doesn't sound like
you're vulnerable to throwing

00:38:44.080 --> 00:38:46.960 align:middle line:84%
in the towel and suicide
like some people are,

00:38:46.960 --> 00:38:49.260 align:middle line:84%
because you have
such a lovely support

00:38:49.260 --> 00:38:51.460 align:middle line:84%
group in your family
and all these women

00:38:51.460 --> 00:38:55.600 align:middle line:84%
and since you have such a strong
spiritual basis to your life.

00:38:55.600 --> 00:38:57.154 align:middle line:90%
You can handle it.

00:38:57.154 --> 00:38:57.820 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Right.

00:38:57.820 --> 00:39:04.080 align:middle line:84%
Although throwing in the towel,
many times I've said, I quit.

00:39:04.080 --> 00:39:05.140 align:middle line:90%
God, why?

00:39:05.140 --> 00:39:07.030 align:middle line:90%
I'm done.

00:39:07.030 --> 00:39:10.500 align:middle line:84%
But then I start thinking,
Jesus would not give up on me.

00:39:10.500 --> 00:39:13.000 align:middle line:84%
So why am I going to
give up on anybody else?

00:39:13.000 --> 00:39:14.990 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so many
people need your help.

00:39:14.990 --> 00:39:16.440 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah.

00:39:16.440 --> 00:39:17.810 align:middle line:90%
And it's not them.

00:39:17.810 --> 00:39:21.740 align:middle line:90%
I need help and other people.

00:39:21.740 --> 00:39:22.960 align:middle line:90%
I would say we're a family.

00:39:22.960 --> 00:39:24.024 align:middle line:90%
We're a team.

00:39:24.024 --> 00:39:25.690 align:middle line:84%
It does take a village
to raise a child.

00:39:25.690 --> 00:39:28.330 align:middle line:90%
It's true.

00:39:28.330 --> 00:39:32.840 align:middle line:84%
The aspects of growing
and throwing that towel,

00:39:32.840 --> 00:39:36.980 align:middle line:84%
for less of a term, I
mean, I couldn't do it.

00:39:36.980 --> 00:39:38.500 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't do it,
because if I did,

00:39:38.500 --> 00:39:44.120 align:middle line:84%
I'm letting down every mom,
dad, or child, grandpa, grandma

00:39:44.120 --> 00:39:45.280 align:middle line:90%
who just want that.

00:39:45.280 --> 00:39:47.152 align:middle line:84%
Just give me five
minutes of your time.

