but I gotta keep it real.

00:42:56.560 --> 00:43:00.160 align:middle line:84%
So we're doing it in
"America's Most Wanted" type

00:43:00.160 --> 00:43:03.960 align:middle line:84%
fashion, "Cops" type fashion,
Robbie Thomas fashion, which

00:43:03.960 --> 00:43:06.200 align:middle line:84%
means you're going to
be on scene with me.

00:43:06.200 --> 00:43:07.666 align:middle line:84%
You're going to
see what I'm doing.

00:43:07.666 --> 00:43:09.290 align:middle line:84%
You're going to see
me reading reports.

00:43:09.290 --> 00:43:11.330 align:middle line:84%
You're going to see the
police talking to me.

00:43:11.330 --> 00:43:13.210 align:middle line:84%
You're going to see
death scene photographs.

00:43:13.210 --> 00:43:15.790 align:middle line:84%
You're going to see
as much as I see,

00:43:15.790 --> 00:43:18.510 align:middle line:84%
and it's all going to
be fast-forward, bang

00:43:18.510 --> 00:43:20.356 align:middle line:90%
in your face, and that's it.

00:43:20.356 --> 00:43:22.875 align:middle line:90%
I think that's a good show.

00:43:22.875 --> 00:43:24.280 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well,
I would think so.

00:43:24.280 --> 00:43:26.640 align:middle line:90%
Is that not dramatic enough?

00:43:26.640 --> 00:43:27.290 align:middle line:90%
Not yet?

00:43:27.290 --> 00:43:28.206 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: No, I guess.

00:43:28.206 --> 00:43:30.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Wow. [LAUGHING]
No, instead we're

00:43:30.880 --> 00:43:33.861 align:middle line:84%
enthralled with whoever "The
Bachelor" is going to marry,

00:43:33.861 --> 00:43:35.235 align:middle line:84%
whoever "The
Bachelor" is anyway.

00:43:35.235 --> 00:43:36.280 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Or some swamp guys.

00:43:36.280 --> 00:43:38.060 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Or some
swamp guys, oh, my God.

00:43:38.060 --> 00:43:40.490 align:middle line:84%
OK, so there are
some other-- I want

00:43:40.490 --> 00:43:42.980 align:middle line:84%
to talk a little bit about
these books in a bit,

00:43:42.980 --> 00:43:46.980 align:middle line:84%
but tell us about what happened
in the Victoria Stafford case.

00:43:46.980 --> 00:43:49.560 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Yeah, there's
a beautiful little girl,

00:43:49.560 --> 00:43:53.370 align:middle line:84%
beautiful girls
everywhere and boys.

00:43:53.370 --> 00:43:54.710 align:middle line:90%
I'm sitting at home.

00:43:54.710 --> 00:43:56.680 align:middle line:84%
My wife is adjacent
from me watching TV.

00:43:56.680 --> 00:43:59.650 align:middle line:90%
And I just get a vision.

00:43:59.650 --> 00:44:01.940 align:middle line:84%
And it's a blond-haired,
beautiful little girl

00:44:01.940 --> 00:44:05.795 align:middle line:84%
walking into the tree line
by a huge pile of rocks.

00:44:05.795 --> 00:44:06.670 align:middle line:90%
So that's all I seen.

00:44:06.670 --> 00:44:08.300 align:middle line:84%
And I said to my
wife, there's gonna

00:44:08.300 --> 00:44:11.830 align:middle line:84%
be another little girl go
missing very, very soon.

00:44:11.830 --> 00:44:13.587 align:middle line:90%
And she said, what?

00:44:13.587 --> 00:44:14.920 align:middle line:90%
And I started explaining to her.

00:44:14.920 --> 00:44:16.880 align:middle line:84%
She goes, oh, no,
hope it's not true.

00:44:16.880 --> 00:44:22.629 align:middle line:84%
Two days later, eight-year-old
Victoria goes missing.

00:44:22.629 --> 00:44:24.420 align:middle line:84%
It's about an hour and
a half from my home.

00:44:24.420 --> 00:44:27.010 align:middle line:90%
It's called Woodstock, Ontario.

00:44:27.010 --> 00:44:29.140 align:middle line:84%
Me and the family
get in contact.

00:44:29.140 --> 00:44:32.750 align:middle line:84%
I go down and meet them, go
meet the Detective Brown.

00:44:32.750 --> 00:44:34.344 align:middle line:84%
I'm in office, and
I'm talking to her.

00:44:34.344 --> 00:44:36.010 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Now, did
you reach out to them

00:44:36.010 --> 00:44:37.410 align:middle line:84%
because you had
already the vision?

00:44:37.410 --> 00:44:37.800 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yes.

00:44:37.800 --> 00:44:38.340 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:44:38.340 --> 00:44:40.060 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you knew
it was going to happen.

00:44:40.060 --> 00:44:41.830 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: I normally don't
reach out to people at all.

00:44:41.830 --> 00:44:42.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:44:42.090 --> 00:44:42.220 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:44:42.220 --> 00:44:44.344 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: They always
contact me through my office.

00:44:44.344 --> 00:44:48.050 align:middle line:84%
So I normally don't go, hey--
because it would disprove--

00:44:48.050 --> 00:44:49.940 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's people
out there who do that,

00:44:49.940 --> 00:44:52.140 align:middle line:84%
and I called them
back door salesman.

00:44:52.140 --> 00:44:53.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, exactly.

00:44:53.170 --> 00:44:55.064 align:middle line:84%
But this one, you had
already had the vision

00:44:55.064 --> 00:44:55.980 align:middle line:90%
of prior to the event.

00:44:55.980 --> 00:44:56.810 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:44:56.810 --> 00:44:58.850 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: So it all hit.

00:44:58.850 --> 00:45:04.126 align:middle line:84%
And I profiled a
woman and a man.

00:45:04.126 --> 00:45:06.250 align:middle line:84%
The police said, no, we're
just looking for a woman

00:45:06.250 --> 00:45:08.090 align:middle line:90%
because we have her on film.

00:45:08.090 --> 00:45:12.230 align:middle line:84%
And they showed the cameras
on the school, a grainy video,

00:45:12.230 --> 00:45:16.442 align:middle line:84%
and it showed a woman leading
Victoria away from the school.

00:45:16.442 --> 00:45:18.400 align:middle line:84%
And I said, no, you're
looking for a man, too/.

00:45:18.400 --> 00:45:20.570 align:middle line:90%
He's the mastermind behind this.

00:45:20.570 --> 00:45:23.450 align:middle line:90%
And I profiled him.

00:45:23.450 --> 00:45:27.680 align:middle line:84%
So it turns out-- I want to
come back into this case,

00:45:27.680 --> 00:45:30.620 align:middle line:84%
but it turns out it was a
man much older than her.

00:45:30.620 --> 00:45:34.200 align:middle line:84%
Profile was perfect,
same with the girl.

00:45:34.200 --> 00:45:37.880 align:middle line:84%
Go back into the
case with the family,

00:45:37.880 --> 00:45:40.250 align:middle line:84%
they plant me in
the mother's house.

00:45:40.250 --> 00:45:43.750 align:middle line:84%
Mother is unbeknownst who
I am, wanting to know.

00:45:43.750 --> 00:45:47.030 align:middle line:84%
And I'm thinking, OK, why aren't
you looking for your child?

00:45:47.030 --> 00:45:51.420 align:middle line:84%
People grieve differently, but
there's not a grieving process

00:45:51.420 --> 00:45:54.530 align:middle line:84%
here, because she's just
missing at the time, right?

00:45:54.530 --> 00:45:55.840 align:middle line:90%
Not once going out.

00:45:55.840 --> 00:45:58.180 align:middle line:84%
And if you're a parent,
you're pounding the floor.

00:45:58.180 --> 00:45:58.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, yeah.

00:45:58.350 --> 00:45:59.370 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: You're
going out there.

00:45:59.370 --> 00:45:59.995 align:middle line:90%
You're looking.

00:45:59.995 --> 00:46:01.345 align:middle line:90%
You're tearing everything up.

00:46:01.345 --> 00:46:03.729 align:middle line:90%


00:46:03.729 --> 00:46:05.520 align:middle line:84%
I gotta catch myself,
because there's still

00:46:05.520 --> 00:46:06.790 align:middle line:90%
more part of this case.

00:46:06.790 --> 00:46:08.957 align:middle line:90%
But I just want to continue.

00:46:08.957 --> 00:46:11.040 align:middle line:84%
I know you can understand
where I'm going on this.

00:46:11.040 --> 00:46:12.545 align:middle line:90%
There's part open still.

00:46:12.545 --> 00:46:13.920 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The case
is still open?

00:46:13.920 --> 00:46:15.160 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Well, there's
part of it that's--

00:46:15.160 --> 00:46:15.900 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: A part
of it's still open?

00:46:15.900 --> 00:46:16.399 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:46:16.399 --> 00:46:21.440 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: So get the
man, girl pleads guilty,

00:46:21.440 --> 00:46:23.890 align:middle line:90%
man found guilty.

00:46:23.890 --> 00:46:25.710 align:middle line:90%
They're off to jail.

00:46:25.710 --> 00:46:28.630 align:middle line:84%
And the funny twist to this,
the man who put McCafferty

00:46:28.630 --> 00:46:34.120 align:middle line:84%
in the car, the detective had
him arrested and arrested him,

00:46:34.120 --> 00:46:36.530 align:middle line:84%
my aunt calls me up-- my
uncle died years ago--

00:46:36.530 --> 00:46:40.320 align:middle line:84%
and she says to me-- she's
not dated for years--

00:46:40.320 --> 00:46:42.910 align:middle line:84%
she goes, you just ain't
gonna believe who I'm dating.

00:46:42.910 --> 00:46:43.700 align:middle line:90%
And I said, who?

00:46:43.700 --> 00:46:44.990 align:middle line:84%
She goes, you know
that case you worked?

00:46:44.990 --> 00:46:46.940 align:middle line:84%
And I said, oh, my gosh,
are you kidding me?

00:46:46.940 --> 00:46:47.940 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: All in the family.

00:46:47.940 --> 00:46:49.080 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: All in
the family, right?

00:46:49.080 --> 00:46:49.996 align:middle line:90%
Keep it in the family.

00:46:49.996 --> 00:46:55.500 align:middle line:84%
But going back to your
question about that,

00:46:55.500 --> 00:46:59.890 align:middle line:84%
when I drew the drawings, the
pile of rocks, the tree line,

00:46:59.890 --> 00:47:03.720 align:middle line:84%
I'd seen wagon wheels,
tons of wagon wheels.

00:47:03.720 --> 00:47:07.360 align:middle line:84%
And I'm trying to discern
all this information quick,

00:47:07.360 --> 00:47:08.687 align:middle line:90%
so I draw it all out.

00:47:08.687 --> 00:47:10.145 align:middle line:84%
And we went hunting
for her, right?

00:47:10.145 --> 00:47:12.640 align:middle line:84%
And we found this one home, and
it was full of wagon wheels.

00:47:12.640 --> 00:47:14.010 align:middle line:84%
And I thought,
that's where she is!

00:47:14.010 --> 00:47:15.176 align:middle line:90%
And I'm going, I don't know.

00:47:15.176 --> 00:47:16.366 align:middle line:90%
Just hang tough.

00:47:16.366 --> 00:47:18.990 align:middle line:84%
But they went in right away, the
police went right in the door,

00:47:18.990 --> 00:47:21.840 align:middle line:90%
and it wasn't where she was.

00:47:21.840 --> 00:47:23.360 align:middle line:90%
Here's the tree line.

00:47:23.360 --> 00:47:24.740 align:middle line:90%
Here's the pile of rocks.

00:47:24.740 --> 00:47:26.620 align:middle line:90%
There's a laneway.

00:47:26.620 --> 00:47:28.616 align:middle line:84%
Down that laneway is
a Mennonite village.

00:47:28.616 --> 00:47:29.740 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, wagon wheels.

00:47:29.740 --> 00:47:31.930 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Wagon wheels,
horse-drawn buggies--

00:47:31.930 --> 00:47:32.480 align:middle line:90%
what I drew.

00:47:32.480 --> 00:47:33.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:47:33.050 --> 00:47:33.570 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah.

00:47:33.570 --> 00:47:34.390 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, my God.

00:47:34.390 --> 00:47:35.660 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: And her body
was found right there

00:47:35.660 --> 00:47:37.070 align:middle line:90%
by the pile of rocks.

00:47:37.070 --> 00:47:38.090 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And see, it
wouldn't make sense

00:47:38.090 --> 00:47:40.300 align:middle line:84%
unless somebody put that piece
together, that's for sure.

00:47:40.300 --> 00:47:40.870 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Right, right.

00:47:40.870 --> 00:47:43.203 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But what about this
piece about the mother who

00:47:43.203 --> 00:47:44.340 align:middle line:90%
wasn't in mourning?

00:47:44.340 --> 00:47:48.760 align:middle line:84%
>>THOMAS: Yeah, I just
find that kind of strange.

00:47:48.760 --> 00:47:50.445 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, to say the least.

00:47:50.445 --> 00:47:51.070 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah.

00:47:51.070 --> 00:47:52.800 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sitting
there, and I'm trying

00:47:52.800 --> 00:47:56.530 align:middle line:84%
to get a read on her and
her boyfriend in the home.

00:47:56.530 --> 00:48:00.440 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking at kids
coming out of the living room,

00:48:00.440 --> 00:48:02.500 align:middle line:84%
and they've got beer
bottles in their hands,

00:48:02.500 --> 00:48:04.920 align:middle line:84%
and they're like
13, 14 years of age.

00:48:04.920 --> 00:48:08.510 align:middle line:84%
OK, I know it's a tough time,
but strange things, right?

00:48:08.510 --> 00:48:10.228 align:middle line:90%
Strange.

00:48:10.228 --> 00:48:11.950 align:middle line:84%
I've been in a lot
of strange places

00:48:11.950 --> 00:48:15.370 align:middle line:84%
and seen a lot of
strange things.

00:48:15.370 --> 00:48:17.250 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So that part
is maybe still open?

00:48:17.250 --> 00:48:17.720 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah.

00:48:17.720 --> 00:48:19.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK,
gotcha on that one.

00:48:19.140 --> 00:48:20.200 align:middle line:84%
All right, we don't
need to go there.

00:48:20.200 --> 00:48:20.741 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: No.

00:48:20.741 --> 00:48:22.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, the Brewer family.

00:48:22.080 --> 00:48:22.704 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Yeah.

00:48:22.704 --> 00:48:25.799 align:middle line:84%
Oh, one more thing about
the Victoria Stafford case.

00:48:25.799 --> 00:48:28.340 align:middle line:84%
Like I told you, I do automatic
hand drawing, and it's there.

00:48:28.340 --> 00:48:29.544 align:middle line:90%
I put "Gulch."

00:48:29.544 --> 00:48:30.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Gulch?

00:48:30.210 --> 00:48:30.500 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:48:30.500 --> 00:48:31.240 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Gulch, right.

00:48:31.240 --> 00:48:32.073 align:middle line:90%
I'm thinking, gulch.

00:48:32.073 --> 00:48:34.100 align:middle line:84%
And I kept telling
the family, gulch.

00:48:34.100 --> 00:48:36.076 align:middle line:84%
But they found her
body near Guelph.

00:48:36.076 --> 00:48:38.522 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh,
Guelph-- interesting.

00:48:38.522 --> 00:48:39.730 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Interesting, right?

00:48:39.730 --> 00:48:41.620 align:middle line:84%
And it's just a
perception, and it's fast,

00:48:41.620 --> 00:48:42.875 align:middle line:90%
and you gotta put it down.

00:48:42.875 --> 00:48:43.500 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:48:43.500 --> 00:48:45.350 align:middle line:84%
I've always been
fascinated with this.

00:48:45.350 --> 00:48:48.910 align:middle line:84%
And as I said in the open of
the show, about 30 years ago

00:48:48.910 --> 00:48:52.180 align:middle line:84%
when I was a news anchor,
when we had sweeps week,

00:48:52.180 --> 00:48:55.150 align:middle line:84%
the ratings, they kind of
let me do what I wanted.

00:48:55.150 --> 00:48:57.030 align:middle line:84%
It's like, hey, go find
something fun to do.

00:48:57.030 --> 00:48:59.299 align:middle line:84%
Go do a special with
some kind of ratings.

00:48:59.299 --> 00:49:00.840 align:middle line:84%
And I was always
drawn to things that

00:49:00.840 --> 00:49:02.770 align:middle line:90%
were metaphysically oriented.

00:49:02.770 --> 00:49:07.450 align:middle line:84%
And that is what I put up that
one week, as I was saying.

00:49:07.450 --> 00:49:09.290 align:middle line:84%
And I became friends
with the woman

00:49:09.290 --> 00:49:13.000 align:middle line:84%
who was the psychic at
the police department

00:49:13.000 --> 00:49:14.470 align:middle line:90%
in a few different cities.

00:49:14.470 --> 00:49:17.330 align:middle line:84%
At this time Sacramento was
using her for their cases

00:49:17.330 --> 00:49:19.340 align:middle line:90%
as well, and she was very good.

00:49:19.340 --> 00:49:23.320 align:middle line:84%
And I found along the way
that with myself, I've

00:49:23.320 --> 00:49:25.440 align:middle line:84%
always kind of dipped
into this and that.

00:49:25.440 --> 00:49:28.550 align:middle line:84%
And it's like if there's
space and quiet and time,

00:49:28.550 --> 00:49:31.840 align:middle line:84%
try my hand at whatever the
modality of awareness was.

00:49:31.840 --> 00:49:33.330 align:middle line:90%
And usually it would work.

00:49:33.330 --> 00:49:37.940 align:middle line:84%
And I found one thing, and that
was speaking to people right

00:49:37.940 --> 00:49:42.010 align:middle line:84%
after they die, within like
a three- to five-day window,

00:49:42.010 --> 00:49:43.730 align:middle line:90%
was pretty easy.

00:49:43.730 --> 00:49:47.460 align:middle line:84%
And speaking to people within
a week before they're born

00:49:47.460 --> 00:49:48.600 align:middle line:90%
is pretty easy.

00:49:48.600 --> 00:49:52.299 align:middle line:84%
So you can talk to the
entity, and they can tell you

00:49:52.299 --> 00:49:53.840 align:middle line:84%
kind of what they're
coming here for,

00:49:53.840 --> 00:49:56.750 align:middle line:84%
what their likes, dislikes,
which parent they're associated

00:49:56.750 --> 00:49:59.160 align:middle line:84%
more with, where their
karma is, or maybe

00:49:59.160 --> 00:50:01.824 align:middle line:84%
even they tell me things
like, I'm really just

00:50:01.824 --> 00:50:02.490 align:middle line:90%
here for my mom.

00:50:02.490 --> 00:50:06.570 align:middle line:84%
My dad's gonna leave before
I'm one, things like that.

00:50:06.570 --> 00:50:08.120 align:middle line:84%
First of all, it's
so interesting

00:50:08.120 --> 00:50:10.890 align:middle line:84%
to note that the
entity coming in

00:50:10.890 --> 00:50:12.489 align:middle line:84%
is fully aware what
the dynamics are.

00:50:12.489 --> 00:50:13.280 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Oh, sure.

00:50:13.280 --> 00:50:14.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: There's no
big shock or surprise.

00:50:14.290 --> 00:50:14.430 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: No.

00:50:14.430 --> 00:50:16.810 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I wouldn't tell the
mother that kind of thing,

00:50:16.810 --> 00:50:17.550 align:middle line:90%
certainly.

00:50:17.550 --> 00:50:19.780 align:middle line:84%
But also right after
they die, but there's

00:50:19.780 --> 00:50:22.270 align:middle line:84%
a point at which some
entities don't stick around.

00:50:22.270 --> 00:50:22.860 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: No.

00:50:22.860 --> 00:50:23.460 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: They go.

00:50:23.460 --> 00:50:24.630 align:middle line:90%
And let's talk about that.

00:50:24.630 --> 00:50:26.330 align:middle line:90%
>>THOMAS: Sure, sure.

00:50:26.330 --> 00:50:30.070 align:middle line:84%
Coming around many times
in many lives and living,

00:50:30.070 --> 00:50:33.560 align:middle line:84%
reincarnation, when I was a
child, I used to say to my mom,

00:50:33.560 --> 00:50:34.512 align:middle line:90%
I'm reincarnated.

00:50:34.512 --> 00:50:35.470 align:middle line:90%
She said, well, really?

00:50:35.470 --> 00:50:37.240 align:middle line:90%
She wanted to know why and how.

00:50:37.240 --> 00:50:39.150 align:middle line:84%
So I would explain, I
lived with my father.

